(30, 1, '2017-09-26 07:27:45', '2017-09-26 07:27:45', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Map</span>  </h1>\n\nThe map interface is one of the most data rich views in the application. It contains a variety of layers, a full set of available filter tools, and access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the Dashboard, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Spatial Filters</span>  </h4>\n\nThere are two types of filters on the DRIVER website: Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters. Spatial Filters are primarily used for the Map interface, and is a geographic boundary filter which is chosen in the page header.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>\n\n• Map View vs List View\n\n• Spatial Filters\n\n• Attribute Filters\n\n', 'Post #28', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-26 07:27:45', '2017-09-26 07:27:45', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(31, 1, '2017-09-26 07:32:07', '2017-09-26 07:32:07', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Map</span>  </h1>\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filters tools, layers, and more. Depending on the type of user, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the Dashboard, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">[GIF]</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Spatial Filters</span>  </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are drawings tool that acts as a geographic boundary filter.&nbsp;While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website - Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters - Spatial Filters are used only for the Map interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>\n\n• Map View vs List View\n\n• Spatial Filters\n\n• Attribute Filters\n\n', 'Post #28', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-26 07:32:07', '2017-09-26 07:32:07', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(32, 1, '2017-09-26 09:25:58', '2017-09-26 09:25:58', '[:en]Spatial Filters are tools that act as geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a> and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface.</a>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-filter\" xlink=\"href\">Region Filter</a></h3>\r\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page. Users may select a Region Filter either on the Map Interface or the Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"798\" height=\"439\" />Once the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/custom-area-filter/\" xlink=\"href\">Custom Area Filter</a></h3>\r\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-388 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/custom-area-filter/\" xlink=\"href\">Custom Area Filter</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a> and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\">Map Interface.</a>\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Spatial Filters and How to Use Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Region Filter</span>  </h4>\r\n\r\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page. Users may select a Region Filter either on the Map Interface or the Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"439\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"798\">Once the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\r\n\r\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/custom-area-filter/\">Custom Area Filter</a></span>  </h4>\r\n\r\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-388 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/custom-area-filter/\">Custom Area Filter</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Spatial Filters', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'spatial-filters', '', '', '2017-10-02 17:14:51', '2017-10-02 17:14:51', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?page_id=32', 0, 'post', '', 0),
