(65, 1, '2017-09-28 07:03:12', '2017-09-28 07:03:12', '\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different Viewing Interfaces can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Application Defaults</span> </h3>\n\nDRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-179 size-large\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-Application-Defaults-1024x442.png\" width=\"835\">\n\n<ol> <li> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days</span> </li> <li> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks3</span> </li> <li> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</span> </li> <li> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days, and;</span> </li> <li> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</span> </li> </ol>\n\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\n\n<h3> Region Default </h3>\n\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-184\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard\'s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to. The default area selected wi\n\n<h3> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a> </h3>\n\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the Map Interface, or the Record List. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\n\n<img alt class=\"size-medium wp-image-184 aligncenter\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">\n\n<h3> <strong>Related Articles</strong> </h3>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 07:09:25', '2017-09-28 07:09:25', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/18-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(66, 1, '2017-09-26 10:01:39', '2017-09-26 10:01:39', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Map</span>  </h1>\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filters tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n[GIF]  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are drawings tool that acts as a geographic boundary filter.&nbsp;While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used only for the Map interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>\n\n• Map View vs List View\n\n<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">• Spatial Filters</a>\n\n• Attribute Filters\n\n', 'Maps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-26 10:01:39', '2017-09-26 10:01:39', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(67, 1, '2017-09-26 10:17:09', '2017-09-26 10:17:09', '<h1>  <strong>Dashboard</strong>  </h1>\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<h3>  <strong>Going Through the Dashboard</strong>  </h3>\n\nDRIVER has 5 principal tools that can be accessed directly through the dashboard. These are (1) Maps, (2) Graphs, (3) Charts, (4) Filters, and (5) Record Lists.\n\n<h4>  <strong><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/maps\">Maps</a></strong>  </h4>\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filters tools, layers, and more. Depending on the type of user, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Record List</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">The record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.</p>  <h4>  Region Defaults  </h4>\n\nBlack Spots by Severity\n\nIncidents\n\nSaved Filters\n\n<h4>  <strong>Graphs</strong>  </h4>\n\nShort introduction of Graphs. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer diam massa, cursus id vestibulum non, commodo vel nisl. Sed vel varius ex.\n\n<h4>  <strong>ToDDoW Chart (Time of Day, Day of Week Chart)</strong>  </h4>\n\nThe two widgets on the top right corner of the DRIVER dashboard are coded as the ToDDoW charts. These charts show the concentration of incidents over the&nbsp;last 90 days. There is also a map of accidents that occurred&nbsp;during the past two weeks, and a map of current black spots,&nbsp;color coded by severity. Two widgets in the top right co\n\n<h4>  <strong>Filters (*)</strong>  </h4>\n\nShort introduction of filters. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer diam massa, cursus id vestibulum non, commodo vel nisl. Sed vel varius ex.\n\n<h4>  <strong>Record List (Link to Record List Article)</strong>  </h4>\n\nShort introduction of record lists. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer diam massa, cursus id vestibulum non, commodo vel nisl. Sed vel varius ex.\n\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Viewing Options (Map View vs List View)  </li>  <li>  Maps  </li>  <li>  Graphs (ToDDoW black spots)  </li>  <li>  Charts  </li>  <li>  Filters  </li>  <li>  Record List  </li>  </ul>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-26 10:17:09', '2017-09-26 10:17:09', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(70, 1, '2017-09-26 10:17:38', '2017-09-26 10:17:38', '[:en]The record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface. From this view, users can access more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit incident data.\r\n<h3>Accessing Incident Records</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-672 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Viewing Incident Data</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on the “View\" button on the right most side of each entry will prompt a popup to appear, which shows users more details of the incident data.</p>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-673 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_02-Filtering_View-Incident.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-675 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Filters_Attribute-Filters-Copy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"103\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Using Filters in the Record List</h3>\r\nFilters may be used to further narrow down incidents on the record list. Filters can be selected on the header bar on top of the Record List.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-372 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"199\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsers may choose a filter or combination of filters to apply on the Record List.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-677 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_04-Filtering_Date-Range-1.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:Ph]\r\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text Search</span>\r\n\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Date Filter</span>\r\n\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Option Filter</span>\r\n\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.&nbsp;Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\r\n\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Record List', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'record-list', '', '', '2017-10-04 11:36:43', '2017-10-04 11:36:43', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?page_id=70', 0, 'post', '', 0),
