(72, 1, '2017-09-27 07:33:16', '2017-09-27 07:33:16', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Record List</span> </h1>\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span> </h3>\n\nTo access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span> </h3> <h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span> </h4>\n\nOn the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”. Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.\n\n<h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span> </h4> <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p> <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p> <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>\n\nUsing Attribute&nbsp;\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span> </h3> <ul> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a> </li> </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 12:12:20', '2017-09-27 12:12:20', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/70-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(73, 1, '2017-09-26 10:57:36', '2017-09-26 10:57:36', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Record List</span>  </h1>\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>\n\nTo access the record list, click on the \"Dashboard\" button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown will appear, after which you may click the \"Record List\" button at the button of the list.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 6px;\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incidents</span></p>\n\nOn the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says \"View\". Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering</span>\n\nThe record list has an toolbar at the top of the page which allows users to filter incidents according to Name/Keywword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.\n\n<pre>^PHOTO OF THIS</pre>\n\nUsers may input any combination of these filters in order to narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.\n\n<pre>(Gif na gumagamit ng Name/Keyword Filter)</pre>  <pre style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">(Gif ng gumagamit ng Date Range filter)</pre>  <pre>(Then show yung \"results\" on the record list after filtering)</pre>  <pre>(Gif na gumagamit nung Reporting Agency)**</pre>  <pre>(Gif na gumagamit ng Main Cause filter)**</pre>  <pre>(Gif na gumagamit ng Severity filter)**</pre>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Incident Data  </li>  <li>  Map View vs List View  </li>  <li>  Filters  </li>  </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-26 10:57:36', '2017-09-26 10:57:36', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2017-09-26 10:58:26', '2017-09-26 10:58:26', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Map</span>  </h1>\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filters tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<pre>Gif of this</pre>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are drawings tool that acts as a geographic boundary filter.&nbsp;While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used only for the Map interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>\n\n• Map View vs List View\n\n<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">• Spatial Filters</a>\n\n• Attribute Filters\n\n', 'Maps', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-26 10:58:26', '2017-09-26 10:58:26', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
