(97, 1, '2017-09-27 04:42:08', '2017-09-27 04:42:08', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">User Roles / Types of Users</span> </h1>\n\nThere are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER. Roles and permissions were defined in order to provide different levels of functionality to different types of users.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Admin</span> </h3>\n\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Analyst</span> </h3>\n\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Public Viewer</span> </h3>\n\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span> </h3>\n\nDashboard\n\nRecord Lists\n\nExporting Data\n\n', 'User Types & Roles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 04:42:08', '2017-09-27 04:42:08', '', 95, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/95-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(98, 1, '2017-09-27 06:12:17', '2017-09-27 06:12:17', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">User Roles / Types of Users</span>  </h1>\n\nThere are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER. Roles and permissions were defined in order to provide different levels of functionality to different types of users.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Admin</span>  </h3>\n\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Analyst</span>  </h3>\n\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Public Viewer</span>  </h3>\n\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Dashboard  </li>  <li>  Record Lists  </li>  <li>  Exporting Data  </li>  </ul>', 'User Types & Roles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 06:12:17', '2017-09-27 06:12:17', '', 95, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(99, 1, '2017-09-27 06:22:12', '2017-09-27 06:22:12', '[:en]The DRIVER website can be found by going to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph</a>. To get access to the DRIVER website, you must have a Google account, or a\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">Signing In</h3>\r\nIf a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button. This process redirects to the provider’s authentication page, and after a successful login, redirects back to DRIVER with the user’s credentials\r\n\r\nAdministrators may also create username and password pairs for users to log in.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-431 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/9_Login_Driver.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1363\" height=\"639\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Sign In</span></h3>\r\nYou’ll need a Google Account before you can sign in to DRIVER. If you already have one, simply click on the “Log in With Google Account” button to proceed to the website.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-432 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Login-Google.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"602\" height=\"77\" />Certain administrators of DRIVER may also create and assign username and password combinations for others. For users who have their own non-Google login details provided by DRIVER administrators, you may simply enter your username and password, click the “Sign In” button, and proceed to the website.[:Ph]\r\nThe DRIVER website can be found by going to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph</a>. To get access to the DRIVER website, you must have a Google account, or a\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">  Signing In  </h3>\r\n\r\nIf a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button. This process redirects to the provider’s authentication page, and after a successful login, redirects back to DRIVER with the user’s credentials\r\n\r\nAdministrators may also create username and password pairs for users to log in.\r\n\r\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter wp-image-431 size-full\" height=\"639\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/9_Login_Driver.png\" width=\"1363\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Sign In</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nYou’ll need a Google Account before you can sign in to DRIVER. If you already have one, simply click on the “Log in With Google Account” button to proceed to the website.\r\n\r\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter wp-image-432 size-full\" height=\"77\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Login-Google.png\" width=\"602\">Certain administrators of DRIVER may also create and assign username and password combinations for others. For users who have their own non-Google login details provided by DRIVER administrators, you may simply enter your username and password, click the “Sign In” button, and proceed to the website.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/get-started\">Get Started</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Accessing DRIVER', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'accessing-driver', '', '', '2017-10-10 06:16:11', '2017-10-10 06:16:11', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?page_id=99', 0, 'post', '', 0),
