(102, 1, '2017-09-27 06:25:12', '2017-09-27 06:25:12', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Signing In</span>  </h1>\n\nIf a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button. This process redirects to the provider’s authentication page, and after a successful login, redirects back to DRIVER with the user’s credentials\n\nAdministrators may also create username and password pairs for users to log in.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Sign In</span>  </h3>\n\nYou’ll need a Google Account before you can sign in to DRIVER. If you already have one, simply click on the “Log in With Google Account” button to proceed to the website.\n\nCertain administrators of DRIVER may also create and assign username and password combinations for others. For users who have their own non-Google login details provided by DRIVER administrators, you may simply enter your username and password, click the “Sign In” button, and proceed to the website.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\">User Types &amp; Roles</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Signing In', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 06:25:12', '2017-09-27 06:25:12', '', 99, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/99-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2017-09-27 06:28:50', '2017-09-27 06:28:50', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h1>\n\nDRIVER provides a variety of ways to interact with the map and list view by using filter and search tools&nbsp;to analyze subsets of the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Attribute Filters</span>  </h3>', 'Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 06:28:50', '2017-09-27 06:28:50', '', 89, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(104, 1, '2017-09-27 06:28:50', '2017-09-27 06:28:50', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span> </h1>\n\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.\n\nThere are two types of filtering &amp; searching features available on DRIVER: attribute filters, and spatial filters.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Attribute Filters</span> </h3>\n\nAttribute filters are filters that are used for the List View function of DRIVER.&nbsp;\n\n', 'Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '89-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 07:13:14', '2017-09-27 07:13:14', '', 89, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/89-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(105, 1, '2017-09-28 05:07:42', '2017-09-28 05:07:42', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Attribute Filters</span> </h1>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\nThere are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Attribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\">The Attribute Filters can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the Record List or Map Interface.</p> <h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\"> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Attribute Filters and How to Access Them</span> </h3> <h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span> </h4>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface. Searching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer. Typing multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span> </h4>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user. &nbsp; Clicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span> </h4>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident). Selecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter. Active filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span> </h4>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span> </h3> <ul> <li> <a href=\"http://filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a> </li> </ul>', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 09:44:56', '2017-09-28 09:44:56', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/40-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2017-09-27 06:52:46', '2017-09-27 06:52:46', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Attribute Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nDRIVER syncs with the database designer schema to make filterable fields available to users. Fields marked as filterable/searchable are included in the filter bar.\n\nThere are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the List View, or the Map View. Attribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for the List View option of the DRIVER website.\n\nThe Attribute Filters can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing the Map.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Attribute Filters and How to Access Them</span>  </h3>  [IMG: The top bar with labels of the types of Attribute Filters]\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer. Typing multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>\n\n[WORD BETTER]\n\nThe date filter has a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range is the previous ninety days.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>\n\nEnumeration fields (select lists, checkboxes) are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Selecting an option applies that filter to the data. Multiple options may be selected for any filter. Active filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>\n\n• List View\n\n• Spatial Filters\n\n• Saving Filters\n\n• Clearing Filters\n\n', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 06:52:46', '2017-09-27 06:52:46', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2017-09-27 06:52:55', '2017-09-27 06:52:55', '[:en]There are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></h3>\r\nAside from acting as the home screen of the site, the dashboard also includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Dashboard.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"636\" />\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></h3>\r\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"638\" />\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></h3>\r\nAside from a more general, visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-318 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full\" height=\"636\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Dashboard.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may 