(118, 1, '2017-09-28 07:19:08', '2017-09-28 07:19:08', '\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span> </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span> </h3> <h3> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/filtering-and-searching/\">Filters</a> </h3> <h3> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/layers/\">Layers</a> </h3>\n\nUsers can further narrow down the map interface by using layers. T to by Street View or Satellite view,\n\n<h3> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/graphs-2/\">Graphs</a> </h3> <h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span> </h4>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others. The Attribute Filters can be used for both the Report List and the Map Interface, and are usually available through a bar on the top of the page.\n\n<h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span> </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used on the Map Interface, and are only available when the Map Interface is accessed.\n\n<h4> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a> </h4>\n\nUsers may create combinations of filters and save them for future use. Additionally, users my also or clear the ones already in use if they prefer to use a different pre-save filter. DRIVER also allows its users the option to delete filters.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span> </h3> <ul> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a> </li> </ul>', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 07:34:33', '2017-09-28 07:34:33', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/28-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(119, 1, '2017-09-27 07:54:09', '2017-09-27 07:54:09', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Attribute Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\nThere are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Attribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\n\nThe Attribute Filters can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the Record List or Map Interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Attribute Filters and How to Access Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface. Searching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer. Typing multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user. &nbsp; Clicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency [concerned in the incident], Main Cause [of incident], and Severity [of incident]. Selecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter. Active filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<h4>  Numeric Filter  </h4>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Filtering &amp; Searching  </li>  <li>  View Interfaces  </li>  <li>  Spatial Filters  </li>  </ul>', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 07:54:09', '2017-09-27 07:54:09', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
