(122, 1, '2017-09-27 08:00:40', '2017-09-27 08:00:40', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Map</span>  </h1>\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filters tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<pre>Gif of this​</pre>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span>  </h4>    <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are drawings tool that acts as a geographic boundary filter.&nbsp;While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used only for the Map interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 08:00:40', '2017-09-27 08:00:40', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', 