(126, 1, '2017-09-27 08:14:37', '2017-09-27 08:14:37', '[:en]The <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a> allows users to draw a custom boundary filter to narrow down incidents that occurred in the selected area.\r\n<h3>Types of Custom Area Filters</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span>\r\n\r\nThe Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using the Rectangular Tool</span>\r\n\r\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\r\n\r\nOnce on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-390 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_03-Highlight-Tool.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />Once selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />Once the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-392 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Polygon Tool</strong>\r\n\r\nThe polygon tool allows the user to draw a more customized visual boundary on the map interface. Like the rectangular tool, the polygon tool will filter incidents and data in the selected area that the polygon was drawn on.\r\n\r\n<strong>Using the Polygon Tool</strong>\r\n\r\nTo start using the polygon tool, on the \"Polygon Tool\" button on the far left area of the map interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-396 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_03-Polygon-Tool_01-Select.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />On the map, select a point in the area you would like to start drawing on. Click once on your chosen point. This will activate the polygon tool. To delete a point in the polygon, simply again on click on the Polygon Tool button on the left side of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-397 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_04-Delete-Polygon-Tool.gif\" width=\"794\" height=\"440\" />\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\">Map Interface</a> allows users to draw a custom boundary filter to narrow down incidents that occurred in the selected area.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Custom Area Filters</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Rectangular Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\r\n\r\nOnce on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-390 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_03-Highlight-Tool.gif\" width=\"800\">Once selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" width=\"800\">Once the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-392 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up-1.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Polygon Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe polygon tool allows the user to draw a more customized visual boundary on the map interface. Like the rectangular tool, the polygon tool will filter incidents and data in the selected area that the polygon was drawn on.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Polygon Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo start using the polygon tool, on the \"Polygon Tool\" button on the far left area of the map interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-396 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_03-Polygon-Tool_01-Select.png\" width=\"800\">On the map, select a point in the area you would like to start drawing on. Click once on your chosen point. This will activate the polygon tool. To delete a point in the polygon, simply again on click on the Polygon Tool button on the left side of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-397 size-full\" height=\"440\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_04-Delete-Polygon-Tool.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"794\">\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h1>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Custom Area Filter', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'custom-area-filter', '', '', '2017-10-02 18:44:10', '2017-10-02 18:44:10', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?page_id=126', 0, 'post', '', 0),
