(128, 1, '2017-09-27 08:25:15', '2017-09-27 08:25:15', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Spatial Filters</span> </h1>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Spatial Filters and How to Use Them</span> </h3> <h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Region Filter</span> </h4>\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page. Once the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.&nbsp;Additionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects \"National Capital Region\" in the Region Filter. This filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\n\n<h4> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Custom Area Filter</span> </h4>\n\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area. The boundary drawing tools are on the left side of the map, and include draw (rectangle or polygon), edit, and delete buttons. A tooltip provides instructions while interacting with the tools.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\ngif here\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\nRectangular Tool\n\nThe Rectangular Drawing Tool lets the user draw a rectangle to narrow down the area they would like to focus on.\n\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\ngif here\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\nCustom Area Filter Directions 2 (Polygon)\n\n</div></div>\n<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span> </h3> <ul> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a> </li> <li> <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a> </li> </ul>', 'Spatial Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 11:43:36', '2017-09-27 11:43:36', '', 32, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/32-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(129, 1, '2017-09-27 08:21:40', '2017-09-27 08:21:40', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h1>\r\n\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of filtering &amp; searching features available on DRIVER: attribute filters, and spatial filters.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Attribute Filters</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAttribute filters are filters that are used for the List View function of DRIVER.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n', 'Filtering & Searching', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 08:21:40', '2017-09-27 08:21:40', '', 89, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
