(141, 1, '2017-09-27 11:46:36', '2017-09-27 11:46:36', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Spatial Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Spatial Filters and How to Use Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Region Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page. Once the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.&nbsp;Additionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects \"National Capital Region\" in the Region Filter. This filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Custom Area Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area. The boundary drawing tools are on the left side of the map, and include draw (rectangle or polygon), edit, and delete buttons. A tooltip provides instructions while interacting with the tools.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\ngif here\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\nRectangular Tool\n\nThe Rectangular Drawing Tool lets the user draw a rectangle to narrow down the area they would like to focus on.\n\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\ngif here\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\nCustom Area Filter Directions 2 (Polygon)\n\n</div></div>\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Spatial Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 11:46:36', '2017-09-27 11:46:36', '', 32, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(142, 1, '2017-09-27 11:47:07', '2017-09-27 11:47:07', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">View Interfaces</span>  </h1>\n\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the dashboard, the record list view, or the map view. All incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'View Interfaces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 11:47:07', '2017-09-27 11:47:07', '', 107, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
