(150, 1, '2017-09-27 12:15:02', '2017-09-27 12:15:02', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Record List</span>  </h1>\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>\n\nTo access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>\n\nOn the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”. Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  Using Filters in the Record List /&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 12:15:02', '2017-09-27 12:15:02', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(153, 1, '2017-09-27 12:18:30', '2017-09-27 12:18:30', '<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Record List</span>  </h1>\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>\n\nTo access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>\n\nOn the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”. Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>  <div data-ce-tag=\"toggle\"><input data-ce-tag=\"toggleradio\" id=\"pbs-toggle-89aser\" type=\"checkbox\">  <label data-ce-tag=\"toggletab\" for=\"pbs-toggle-89aser\">  Text Search  </label>  <div class=\"pbs-row\"><div class=\"pbs-col\">\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface. Searching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer. Typing multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n</div></div></div>\n<div data-ce-tag=\"toggle\"><input data-ce-tag=\"toggleradio\" id=\"pbs-toggle-nd36jq\" type=\"checkbox\">  <label data-ce-tag=\"toggletab\" for=\"pbs-toggle-nd36jq\">  Date Filter  </label>  <div class=\"pbs-row\"><div class=\"pbs-col\">\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user. Clicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n</div></div></div>\n<div data-ce-tag=\"toggle\"><input data-ce-tag=\"toggleradio\" id=\"pbs-toggle-ptvs10\" type=\"checkbox\">  <label data-ce-tag=\"toggletab\" for=\"pbs-toggle-ptvs10\">  Option Filter  </label>  <div class=\"pbs-row\"><div class=\"pbs-col\">\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident). Selecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter. Active filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n</div></div></div>\n<div data-ce-tag=\"toggle\"><input data-ce-tag=\"toggleradio\" id=\"pbs-toggle-i93vk7\" type=\"checkbox\">  <label data-ce-tag=\"toggletab\" for=\"pbs-toggle-i93vk7\">  Numeric Filter  </label>  <div class=\"pbs-row\"><div class=\"pbs-col\">\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n</div></div></div>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-27 12:18:30', '2017-09-27 12:18:30', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
