(176, 1, '2017-09-28 05:44:39', '2017-09-28 05:44:39', '\n\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the dashboard, the record list view, or the map interface.\n\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'View Interfaces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 05:44:39', '2017-09-28 05:44:39', '', 107, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(177, 1, '2017-09-28 05:45:24', '2017-09-28 05:45:24', '\n\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the dashboard, the record list view, or the map interface.\n\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'View Interfaces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 05:45:24', '2017-09-28 05:45:24', '', 107, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(178, 1, '2017-09-28 06:18:23', '2017-09-28 06:18:23', '\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<h3>  <strong>Going Through the Dashboard</strong>  </h3>  <h4>  Application Defaults  </h4>\n\nDRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard. These are\n\n<ol>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks3</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</span>  </li>  </ol>  <h4>  <strong><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/maps\">Map</a></strong>  </h4>\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filters tools, layers, and more. Depending on the type of user, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\nThe Map can be accessed by simply clicking the “Dashboard” button on the upper left corner of the DRIVER dashboard. From here, a dropdown will appear with the list of available <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">view interfaces</a>. Click on the button that says “Map.”\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">The record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface. From the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or -depending on the type of user- edit the incident data.</p>  <h4>  Region Defaults  </h4>\n\nBlack Spots by Severity\n\nIncidents\n\nSaved Filters\n\n<h4>  <strong>Graphs</strong>  </h4>\n\nShort introduction of Graphs. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer diam massa, cursus id vestibulum non, commodo vel nisl. Sed vel varius ex.\n\n<h4>  <strong>ToDDoW Chart (Time of Day, Day of Week Chart)</strong>  </h4>\n\nThe two widgets on the top right corner of the DRIVER dashboard are coded as the ToDDoW charts. These charts show the concentration of incidents over the&nbsp;last 90 days. There is also a map of accidents that occurred&nbsp;during the past two weeks, and a map of current black spots,&nbsp;color coded by severity. Two widgets in the top right co\n\n<h4>  <strong>Filters (*)</strong>  </h4>\n\nShort introduction of filters. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer diam massa, cursus id vestibulum non, commodo vel nisl. Sed vel varius ex.\n\n<h4>  <strong>Record List (Link to Record List Article)</strong>  </h4>\n\nShort introduction of record lists. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer diam massa, cursus id vestibulum non, commodo vel nisl. Sed vel varius ex.\n\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Viewing Options (Map View vs List View)  </li>  <li>  Maps  </li>  <li>  Graphs (ToDDoW black spots)  </li>  <li>  Charts  </li>  <li>  Filters  </li>  <li>  Record List  </li>  </ul>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 06:18:23', '2017-09-28 06:18:23', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
