(185, 1, '2017-09-28 07:10:51', '2017-09-28 07:10:51', '\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different Viewing Interfaces can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Application Defaults</span>  </h3>\n\nDRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-179 size-large\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-Application-Defaults-1024x442.png\" width=\"835\">\n\n<ol>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks3</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</span>  </li>  </ol>\n\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\n\n<h3>  Region Default  </h3>\n\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-184\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard\'s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\n\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\n\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the Map Interface, or the Record List. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\n\n<img alt class=\"size-medium wp-image-184 aligncenter\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">\n\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  View Interfaces  </li>  <li>  Filtering &amp; Searching  </li>  </ul>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 07:10:51', '2017-09-28 07:10:51', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2017-09-28 07:11:31', '2017-09-28 07:11:31', '\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different Viewing Interfaces can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Application Defaults</span>  </h3>\n\nDRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-179 size-large\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-Application-Defaults-1024x442.png\" width=\"835\">\n\n<ol>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks3</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</span>  </li>  </ol>\n\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\n\n<h3>  Region Default  </h3>\n\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-184\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard\'s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\n\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\n\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the Map Interface, or the Record List. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\n\n<img alt class=\"size-medium wp-image-184 aligncenter\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">\n\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 07:11:31', '2017-09-28 07:11:31', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(188, 1, '2017-09-28 07:14:13', '2017-09-28 07:14:13', '\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h3>  Filters  </h3>    <h3>  Layers  </h3>  <h3>  Graphs  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others. The Attribute Filters can be used for both the Report List and the Map Interface, and are usually available through a bar on the top of the page.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used on the Map Interface, and are only available when the Map Interface is accessed.\n\n<h4>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </h4>\n\nUsers may create combinations of filters and save them for future use. Additionally, users my also or clear the ones already in use if they prefer to use a different pre-save filter. DRIVER also allows its users the option to delete filters.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 07:14:13', '2017-09-28 07:14:13', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(190, 1, '2017-09-28 07:15:29', '2017-09-28 07:15:29', '\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/filtering-and-searching/\">Filters</a>  </h3>  <h3>  Layers  </h3>  <h3>  Graphs  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others. The Attribute Filters can be used for both the Report List and the Map Interface, and are usually available through a bar on the top of the page.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h4>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used on the Map Interface, and are only available when the Map Interface is accessed.\n\n<h4>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </h4>\n\nUsers may create combinations of filters and save them for future use. Additionally, users my also or clear the ones already in use if they prefer to use a different pre-save filter. DRIVER also allows its users the option to delete filters.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 07:15:29', '2017-09-28 07:15:29', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(193, 1, '2017-09-28 07:18:12', '2017-09-28 07:18:12', '[:en]Aside from filters, users may also narrow down incident data according to layers.\r\n\r\nLayers allow users access to non-incident related data, such as interventions by enforcers, road vulnerability in relation to crashes, or volume of incidents according to severity.\r\n\r\nUsers can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n<h3>Accessing Layers</h3>\r\nOn the map, layers can be accessed by selecting the Layer button on the top right side of the map, below the Saved Filters and Clear Filters button.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-637 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_08-Layers.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Using Filters with Layers</h3>\r\nDRIVER\'s filters may also be used alongside the layers. This can be done by choosing a layer, and then selecting a filter afterward from the white header bar on the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-641 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_10-Layers-Filter-Severity.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:Ph]\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\r\n\r\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Incident data includes:\r\n\r\n<ul>  <li>  The date and time of the incident’s occurrence  </li>  <li>  The location of the incident  </li>  <li>  The time and date of when the incident was added to the DRIVER database  </li>  <li>  Longitude &amp; Latitude  </li>  <li>  Weather during the incident  </li>  <li>  Light (if the incident occurred during the evening or the morning)  </li>  <li>  Severity  </li>  <li>  Collission Type  </li>  <li>  Reporting Agency  </li>  <li>  Location Approximate, and  </li>  <li>  Additional details of the incident  </li>  </ul>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\r\n\r\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'layers', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:08:28', '2017-10-03 17:08:28', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=193', 0, 'post', '', 0),
