(229, 1, '2017-09-28 09:44:20', '2017-09-28 09:44:20', '\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.&nbsp;Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 09:44:20', '2017-09-28 09:44:20', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(230, 1, '2017-09-28 09:48:12', '2017-09-28 09:48:12', '<p style=\"margin-top: -1px;\">DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.</p>\n\nWhile there are two <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a> on the DRIVER website (<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a> &amp; <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>), there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters.</a>\n\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used for the Map Interface.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Filters</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h3>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></span>  </h3>\n\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h1 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using Filters with Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  View Interfaces  </li>  <li>  Attribute Filters  </li>  <li>  Spatial Filters  </li>  <li>  Saving &amp; Clearing Filters  </li>  </ul>', 'Filtering & Searching', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 09:48:12', '2017-09-28 09:48:12', '', 89, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(231, 1, '2017-09-28 10:01:47', '2017-09-28 10:01:47', '\n\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters. This can be useful for defining a combination of filters used to create reports, exports, or other analysis tasks.\n\nSaved filters do not apply to geographic boundary selections or date ranges, but act on search, option, and spatial filters.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Saving Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nAny chosen set of filters can be saved for later use.\n\nTo save a filter, simply click the \"Saved Filters\" button on the top right corner of the screen.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nA pop-up should appear that shows the user\'s saved filters (if any). Below, you\'ll find a box that says \"Add New Saved Filter.\"\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nEnter your desired Filter name, and click on \"Save Filter.\" The new saved filter should now appear inside the pop up.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Clearing Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nFilters may be reset to default state by clicking the clear filter button on the top right corner of the screen, next to the Saved Filters button.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">• Map View vs List View<br> • Spatial Filters<br> • Attribute Filters</p>', 'Saving & Clearing Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '45-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 10:01:47', '2017-09-28 10:01:47', '', 45, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/45-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(232, 1, '2017-09-28 10:02:41', '2017-09-28 10:02:41', '\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Spatial Filters and How to Use Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Region Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page. Once the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.&nbsp;Additionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects “National Capital Region” in the Region Filter. This filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Custom Area Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area. The boundary drawing tools are on the left side of the map, and include draw (rectangle or polygon), edit, and delete buttons. A tooltip provides instructions while interacting with the tools.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\ngif here\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\nRectangular Tool\n\nThe Rectangular Drawing Tool lets the user draw a rectangle to narrow down the area they would like to focus on.\n\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\ngif here\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\nCustom Area Filter Directions 2 (Polygon)\n\n</div></div>\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Spatial Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 10:02:41', '2017-09-28 10:02:41', '', 32, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
