(236, 1, '2017-09-28 10:12:17', '2017-09-28 10:12:17', '\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Spatial Filters and How to Use Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Region Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nOnce the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Custom Area Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">Polygon Tool</span>\n\n</div></div>\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">R</a>egion Filter  </li>  <li>  Custom Area Filter  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Spatial Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 10:12:17', '2017-09-28 10:12:17', '', 32, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(237, 1, '2017-09-28 10:16:02', '2017-09-28 10:16:02', '\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\nThey can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the Record List or Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nThere are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Unlike the Map Interface, Attribute Filters are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map Interface)</span>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Record List)</span>\n\n</div></div>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Attribute Filters and How to Access Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user. &nbsp; Clicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident). Selecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter. Active filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 10:16:02', '2017-09-28 10:16:02', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(238, 1, '2017-09-28 10:17:24', '2017-09-28 10:17:24', '\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\nThey can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the Record List or Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nThere are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Unlike the Map Interface, Attribute Filters are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map Interface)</span>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Record List)</span>\n\n</div></div>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h1>  Types of Attribute Filters and How to Access Them  </h1>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nExamples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\n\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 10:17:24', '2017-09-28 10:17:24', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(240, 1, '2017-09-29 10:24:08', '2017-09-29 10:24:08', '\n\nLayers provide the user with additional tools to further narrow down incident results, and allow the users to view other available data from DRIVER such as blackspots, interventions, and city and region boundaries, among others. The layer tool allows gives users the ability to choose between the conventional streetview of the map, or a satellite view.\n\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span> </h1> <h3> Street View </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3> Satelite View </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h1> <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span> </h1> <h3> Incidents </h3>\n\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Incident data includes:\n\n<ul> <li> The date and time of the incident’s occurrence </li> <li> The location of the incident </li> <li> The time and date of when the incident was added to the DRIVER database </li> <li> Longitude &amp; Latitude </li> <li> Weather during the incident </li> <li> Light (if the incident occurred during the evening or the morning) </li> <li> Severity </li> <li> Collission Type </li> <li> Reporting Agency </li> <li> Location Approximate, and </li> <li> Additional details of the incident </li> </ul>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\n\n<h3> Interventions </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3> Heatmap </h3>\n\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3> Blackspots </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3> City/Province </h3>\n\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3> Region </h3>\n\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 10:54:51', '2017-09-29 10:54:51', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/193-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(241, 1, '2017-09-28 10:42:03', '2017-09-28 10:42:03', '<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 10:42:03', '2017-09-28 10:42:03', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(244, 1, '2017-09-28 11:25:29', '2017-09-28 11:25:29', '<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a more detailed, satellite view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both views.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:25:29', '2017-09-28 11:25:29', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(245, 1, '2017-09-28 11:26:39', '2017-09-28 11:26:39', '[:en]Occasionally, two users may input the same incident. DRIVER has a process that runs on record creation and nightly to identify potential duplicate incidents. Admin and Analyst users may access an interface to identify and resolve the duplicates.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-440 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Manage-Duplicate-Records.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAfter choosing to resolve a potential duplicate, the users are presented with data from each record, and may choose to use one or the other, or keep both records.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-439 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Manage-Duplicate-Records-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1366\" height=\"637\" />[:Ph]\r\nOccasionally, two users may input the same incident. DRIVER has a process that runs on record creation and nightly to identify potential duplicate incidents. Admin users may access an interface to identify and resolve the duplicates.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nAfter choosing to resolve a potential duplicate, the users are presented with data from each record, and may choose to use one or the other, or keep both records.\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Duplicate Record Management[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'duplicate-record-management', '', '', '2017-10-04 06:35:10', '2017-10-04 06:35:10', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=245', 0, 'post', '', 0),
