(250, 1, '2017-09-28 11:31:57', '2017-09-28 11:31:57', '\n\nThe DRIVER application includes functionality to generate custom reports from the database. These reports aggregate counts of incidents according to the rows and columns defined by users generating the reports. The reports also allow for geographic aggregation based on any uploaded boundary layers.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nReports are generated from the map page by clicking Export &gt; Custom Report.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nThe user is presented with a pop-up window that provides the option to select rows and columns from the data fields defined in the schema.\n\nThe user is also able to specify a geographic aggregation to break the\n\ncounts of incidents out by the regions of a boundary layer. Note that\n\nany filters that are active for the application will apply to the results of\n\nthe report.\n\n', 'Reporting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '248-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:31:57', '2017-09-28 11:31:57', '', 248, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/248-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(251, 1, '2017-09-28 11:32:57', '2017-09-28 11:32:57', '\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page.\n\nOnce the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\n\nAdditionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects “National Capital Region” in the Region Filter.\n\nThis filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\n\n', '[:en]Region Filter[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '233-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:32:57', '2017-09-28 11:32:57', '', 233, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/233-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(252, 1, '2017-09-28 11:37:06', '2017-09-28 11:37:06', '\n\nThe Map Interface allows users to draw a custom boundary filter to narrow down incidents that occurred in the selected area.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Custom Area Filters and How to Use Them</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span>  </h3>\n\nThe Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Rectangular Tool</span>  </h3>\n\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"color:#fd3d3f;\">GIF HERE</span>  </h1>\n\nOnce on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"color:#fd3d3f;\">GIF HERE</span>  </h1>\n\nOnce selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"color:#fd3d3f;\">GIF HERE</span>  </h1>\n\nOnce the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"color:#fd3d3f;\">GIF HERE</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Polygon Tool</span>  </h3>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Polygon Tool</span>  </h3>  <h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h1>  <ul>  <li>  Spatial Filters  </li>  <li>  Filtering &amp; Searching  </li>  <li>  View Interfaces  </li>  </ul>', 'Custom Area Filter', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:37:06', '2017-09-28 11:37:06', '', 126, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(253, 1, '2017-09-28 11:38:10', '2017-09-28 11:38:10', '\n\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the dashboard, the record list view, or the map interface.\n\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Dashboard  </li>  <li>  Record List  </li>  <li>  Map  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">F</a>iltering &amp; Searching  </li>  </ul>', 'View Interfaces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:38:10', '2017-09-28 11:38:10', '', 107, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(254, 1, '2017-09-28 11:40:12', '2017-09-28 11:40:12', '\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different Viewing Interfaces can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Application Defaults</span>  </h3>\n\nDRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-179 size-large\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-Application-Defaults-1024x442.png\" width=\"835\">\n\n<ol>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks3</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</span>  </li>  </ol>\n\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\n\n<h3>  Region Default  </h3>\n\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-184\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\n\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\n\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the Map Interface, or the Record List. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\n\n<img alt class=\"size-medium wp-image-184 aligncenter\" height=\"206\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/DRIVER-gif-here-1-300x206.png\" width=\"300\">\n\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  Map Interface  </li>  <li>  Record List  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:40:12', '2017-09-28 11:40:12', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(255, 1, '2017-09-28 11:41:13', '2017-09-28 11:41:13', '\n\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\n\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/layers/\">Layers</a>  </h3>\n\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:&nbsp; Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.&nbsp; Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/27/filtering-and-searching/\">Filters</a>  </h3>\n\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/graphs-2/\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\n\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\n\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\n\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\n\nThe second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:41:13', '2017-09-28 11:41:13', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(256, 1, '2017-09-28 11:43:54', '2017-09-28 11:43:54', '\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.&nbsp;Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  Attribute Filters  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:43:54', '2017-09-28 11:43:54', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(257, 1, '2017-09-28 11:48:10', '2017-09-28 11:48:10', '\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\nThey can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the Record List or Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nThere are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Unlike the Map Interface, Attribute Filters are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map Interface)</span>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Record List)</span>\n\n</div></div>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h1>  Types of Attribute Filters and How to Access Them  </h1>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nExamples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\n\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  View Interfaces  </li>  </ul>', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:48:10', '2017-09-28 11:48:10', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 