(259, 1, '2017-09-28 11:51:17', '2017-09-28 11:51:17', '\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Spatial Filters and How to Use Them</span>  </h3>  <h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Region Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nOnce the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Custom Area Filter</span>  </h4>\n\nCustom Area Filters allow users to draw a custom boundary on the Map Interface in order to filter down to incidents that occurred in that area.\n\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span>\n\n</div>\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">Polygon Tool</span>\n\n</div></div>\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Custom Area Filter  </li>  <li>  Filtering &amp; Searching  </li>  <li>  Saving &amp; Clearing Filters  </li>  <li>  Map Interface  </li>  </ul>', 'Spatial Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-28 11:51:17', '2017-09-28 11:51:17', '', 32, 'http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/28/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
