(308, 1, '2017-09-29 07:54:08', '2017-09-29 07:54:08', '<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the \"Layers\" option on the upper right corner of the map.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\n\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website.&nbsp;\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 07:54:08', '2017-09-29 07:54:08', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(309, 1, '2017-09-29 08:10:12', '2017-09-29 08:10:12', '\n\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters. This can be useful for defining a combination of filters used to create reports, exports, or other analysis tasks.\n\nSaved filters do not apply to geographic boundary selections or date ranges, but act on search, option, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">spatial filters.</a>\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Saving Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nAny chosen set of filters can be saved for later use.\n\nTo save a filter, simply click the “Saved Filters” button on the top right corner of the screen.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">REQUESTED</span>\n\nA pop-up should appear that shows the user’s saved filters (if any). Below, you’ll find a box that says “Add New Saved Filter.”\n\n<b><u>MINE</u></b>\n\nEnter your desired Filter name, and click on “Save Filter.” The new saved filter should now appear inside the pop up.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">REQUESTED</span>\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Clearing Filters</span>  </h1>\n\nFilters may be reset to default state by clicking the clear filter button on the top right corner of the screen, next to the Saved Filters button.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Saving & Clearing Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '45-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 08:10:12', '2017-09-29 08:10:12', '', 45, 'http://roadsafety.ph/45-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
