li>  </ul>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\n\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\n\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\n\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 11:09:19', '2017-09-29 11:09:19', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(341, 1, '2017-09-29 11:26:08', '2017-09-29 11:26:08', '[:en]The DRIVER application includes functionality to generate custom reports from the database. These reports aggregate counts of incidents according to the rows and columns defined by users generating the reports. The reports also allow for geographic aggregation based on any uploaded boundary layers.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nReports are generated from the map page by clicking Export &gt; Custom Report.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nThe user is presented with a pop-up window that provides the option to select rows and columns from the data fields defined in the schema.\r\n\r\nThe user is also able to specify a geographic aggregation to break the counts of incidents out by the regions of a boundary layer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note that any filters that are active for the application will apply to the results of the report.</span>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Exporting Data</li>\r\n 	<li>User Types &amp; Roles</li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe DRIVER application includes functionality to generate custom reports from the database. These reports aggregate counts of incidents according to the rows and columns defined by users generating the reports. The reports also allow for geographic aggregation based on any uploaded boundary layers.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nReports are generated from the map page by clicking Export &gt; Custom Report.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nThe user is presented with a pop-up window that provides the option to select rows and columns from the data fields defined in the schema.\r\n\r\nThe user is also able to specify a geographic aggregation to break the counts of incidents out by the regions of a boundary layer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Note that any filters that are active for the application will apply to the results of the report.</span>\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h1>  <ul>  <li>  Exporting Data  </li>  <li>  User Types &amp; Roles  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Reporting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '248-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 11:26:08', '2017-09-29 11:26:08', '', 248, 'http://roadsafety.ph/248-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(342, 1, '2017-09-29 11:28:40', '2017-09-29 11:28:40', '[:en]<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\r\n<h1><b>Getting Started</b></h1>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DRIVER is designed to collect and analyze data about incidents that occur at a particular place, such as traffic accidents or crimes. The application provides data entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.</span>\r\n<h3><b>Related Articles</b></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Signing In</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User Roles/Types of Users</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dashboard</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maps</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Entering Data</span></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\r\n<h1>  <b>Getting Started</b>  </h1>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DRIVER is designed to collect and analyze data about incidents that occur at a particular place, such as traffic accidents or crimes. The application provides data entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  <b>Related Articles</b>  </h3>  <ul>  <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Signing In</span>  </li>  <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">User Roles/Types of Users</span>  </li>  <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dashboard</span>  </li>  <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maps</span>  </li>  <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Entering Data</span>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]To Trash[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 11:28:40', '2017-09-29 11:28:40', '', 16, 'http://roadsafety.ph/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(343, 1, '2017-09-29 11:35:51', '2017-09-29 11:35:51', '[:en]The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Map</span></h3>\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Important Map Tools</span></h3>\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></h3>\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:  Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.  Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a></h3>\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></h3>\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\nThe second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\">Layers</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:&nbsp; Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.&nbsp; Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filters</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\nThe second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 11:35:51', '2017-09-29 11:35:51', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
