(371, 1, '2017-09-29 12:27:05', '2017-09-29 12:27:05', '\n\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>.\n\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full\" height=\"636\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Dashboard.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" height=\"638\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-318 size-full\" height=\"637\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'View Interfaces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 12:27:05', '2017-09-29 12:27:05', '', 107, 'http://roadsafety.ph/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
