(376, 1, '2017-09-29 12:35:53', '2017-09-29 12:35:53', '<p style=\"margin-top: -1px;\">DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.</p>\n\nWhile there are two <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a> on the DRIVER website (<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a> &amp; <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>), there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters.</a>\n\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used for the Map Interface.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Filters</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span>  </h3>\n\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-372 size-full\" height=\"196\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01-1.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"788\">\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h3>\n\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-373 size-full\" height=\"194\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_02.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"780\">\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></span>  </h3>\n\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters.\n\nYou may save filters and access previously saved filters by clicking on the \"Saved Filters\" icon as shown below:\n\n<img class=\"wp-image-375 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"200\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_03.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"805\">To clear filters or set filters back to their defaults, click the \"Clear Filters\" button\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-374 size-full\" height=\"197\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_04.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"792\">\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Filtering & Searching', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 12:35:53', '2017-09-29 12:35:53', '', 89, 'http://roadsafety.ph/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
