(423, 1, '2017-09-29 13:46:29', '2017-09-29 13:46:29', '[:en]Applied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters. This can be useful for defining a combination of filters used to create reports, exports, or other analysis tasks.\r\n\r\nSaved filters do not apply to geographic boundary selections or date ranges, but act on search, option, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">spatial filters.</a>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Saving Filters</span></h1>\r\nAny chosen set of filters can be saved for later use.\r\n\r\nTo save a filter, simply click the “Saved Filters” button on the top right corner of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-375 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_03.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"199\" />\r\n\r\nA pop-up should appear that shows the user’s saved filters (if any). Below, you’ll find a box that says “Add New Saved Filter.”\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEnter your desired Filter name, and click on “Save Filter.” The new saved filter should now appear inside the pop up.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">REQUESTED</span>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Clearing Filters</span></h1>\r\nFilters may be reset to default state by clicking the clear filter button on the top right corner of the screen, next to the Saved Filters button.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters. This can be useful for defining a combination of filters used to create reports, exports, or other analysis tasks.\r\n\r\nSaved filters do not apply to geographic boundary selections or date ranges, but act on search, option, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">spatial filters.</a>\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Saving Filters</span>  </h1>\r\n\r\nAny chosen set of filters can be saved for later use.\r\n\r\nTo save a filter, simply click the “Saved Filters” button on the top right corner of the screen.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">REQUESTED</span>\r\n\r\nA pop-up should appear that shows the user’s saved filters (if any). Below, you’ll find a box that says “Add New Saved Filter.”\r\n\r\n<b><u>MINE</u></b>\r\n\r\nEnter your desired Filter name, and click on “Save Filter.” The new saved filter should now appear inside the pop up.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">REQUESTED</span>\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Clearing Filters</span>  </h1>\r\n\r\nFilters may be reset to default state by clicking the clear filter button on the top right corner of the screen, next to the Saved Filters button.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Saving & Clearing Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '45-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 13:46:29', '2017-09-29 13:46:29', '', 45, 'http://roadsafety.ph/45-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(430, 1, '2017-09-29 13:58:45', '2017-09-29 13:58:45', '[:en]<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\r\n\r\nIf a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button. This process redirects to the provider’s authentication page, and after a successful login, redirects back to DRIVER with the user’s credentials\r\n\r\nAdministrators may also create username and password pairs for users to log in.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Sign In</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nYou’ll need a Google Account before you can sign in to DRIVER. If you already have one, simply click on the “Log in With Google Account” button to proceed to the website.\r\n\r\nCertain administrators of DRIVER may also create and assign username and password combinations for others. For users who have their own non-Google login details provided by DRIVER administrators, you may simply enter your username and password, click the “Sign In” button, and proceed to the website.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\">User Types &amp; Roles</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/getting-started/\">Getting Started</a>  </li>  </ul>[:Ph]<div data-ce-tag=\"spacer\"></div>\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Signing In</span>  </h1>\r\n\r\nIf a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button. This process redirects to the provider’s authentication page, and after a successful login, redirects back to DRIVER with the user’s credentials\r\n\r\nAdministrators may also create username and password pairs for users to log in.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Sign In</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nYou’ll need a Google Account before you can sign in to DRIVER. If you already have one, simply click on the “Log in With Google Account” button to proceed 