(434, 1, '2017-09-29 14:04:32', '2017-09-29 14:04:32', '[:en]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each \"user type\" or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Admin</span></h3>\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Analyst</span></h3>\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Public Viewer</span></h3>\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/getting-started/\" xlink=\"href\">Getting Started</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record Lists</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThere are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each \"user type\" or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Admin</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Analyst</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Public Viewer</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/getting-started/\">Getting Started</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record Lists</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'User Types & Roles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-09-29 14:04:32', '2017-09-29 14:04:32', '', 95, 'http://roadsafety.ph/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(435, 1, '2017-09-29 14:07:42', '2017-09-29 14:07:42', '\n\nThere are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each “user type” or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-admin\">Admin</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://driver-analyst\">Analyst</a></span>  </h3>\n\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-public-viewer\">Public Viewer</a></span>  </h3>\n\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/getting-started/\" xlink=\"href\">Getting Started</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-admin\">Admin</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-analyst\">Analyst</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-public-viewer\">Public Viewer</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'User Types & Roles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1'