(450, 1, '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Street View</span>  </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n', '[:en]Native Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '448-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '', 448, 'http://roadsafety.ph/448-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(451, 1, '2017-10-02 03:13:43', '2017-10-02 03:13:43', '\n\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\n\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Incident data includes:\n\n<ul>  <li>  The date and time of the incident’s occurrence  </li>  <li>  The location of the incident  </li>  <li>  The time and date of when the incident was added to the DRIVER database  </li>  <li>  Longitude &amp; Latitude  </li>  <li>  Weather during the incident  </li>  <li>  Light (if the incident occurred during the evening or the morning)  </li>  <li>  Severity  </li>  <li>  Collission Type  </li>  <li>  Reporting Agency  </li>  <li>  Location Approximate, and  </li>  <li>  Additional details of the incident  </li>  </ul>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\n\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\n\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\n\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\n\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\n\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\n\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\n\n', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 03:13:43', '2017-10-02 03:13:43', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(453, 1, '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '<h3> <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Street View</span> </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3> Satelite View </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3> Related Notes </h3>', '[:en]Native Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '448-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '2017-10-02 03:12:05', '', 448, 'http://roadsafety.ph/448-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(454, 1, '2017-10-02 03:36:35', '2017-10-02 03:36:35', '<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">Street View</span>  </h3>\n\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\n\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\n\n<h3>  Related Notes  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  Layers  </li>  <li>  Geographic Boundaries  </li>  </ul>', '[:en]Native Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '448-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 03:36:35', '2017-10-02 03:36:35', '', 448, 'http://roadsafety.ph/448-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(455, 1, '2017-10-02 03:55:01', '2017-10-02 03:55:01', '[:en]<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li>The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\" xlink=\"href\">Region Default</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]Application Defaults[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'application-defaults', '', '', '2017-10-02 15:50:40', '2017-10-02 15:50:40', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=455', 0, 'post', '', 0),
