(457, 1, '2017-10-02 04:00:30', '2017-10-02 04:00:30', '\n\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\">Application Defaults</a></span>  </h3>\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\n\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\n\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Region Default</a>  </h3>\n\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\n\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\n\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\"> Map Interface</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\n\nTo access the Map Interface, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\n\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 04:00:30', '2017-10-02 04:00:30', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(458, 1, '2017-10-02 04:02:21', '2017-10-02 04:02:21', '\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\n\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\n\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\n\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </li>  </ul>', '[:en]Application Defaults[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '455-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 04:02:21', '2017-10-02 04:02:21', '', 455, 'http://roadsafety.ph/455-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(459, 1, '2017-10-02 04:07:15', '2017-10-02 04:07:15', '\n\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page.\n\nOnce the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\n\nAdditionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects “National Capital Region” in the Region Filter.\n\nThis filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-362 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">', '[:en]Region Filter[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '233-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 04:07:15', '2017-10-02 04:07:15', '', 233, 'http://roadsafety.ph/233-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
