(486, 1, '2017-10-02 05:27:49', '2017-10-02 05:27:49', '[:en]The dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\" xlink=\"href\">Application Defaults</a></span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span></li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Region Default</a></h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to. The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></h3>\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map Interface</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map Interface, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Related Articles</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\">Application Defaults</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight:normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Region Default</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\"> Map Interface</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map Interface, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 05:27:49', '2017-10-02 05:27:49', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(487, 1, '2017-10-02 05:28:29', '2017-10-02 05:28:29', '\n\nDRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\n\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\n\nTo access driver,&nbsp;\n\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://http\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 05:28:29', '2017-10-02 05:28:29', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(488, 1, '2017-10-02 05:28:34', '2017-10-02 05:28:34', '[:en]The record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span></h3>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span></h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text Search</span>\r\n\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Date Filter</span>\r\n\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Option Filter</span>\r\n\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\r\n\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li>Attribute Filters</li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Text Search</span>\r\n\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Date Filter</span>\r\n\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Option Filter</span>\r\n\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.&nbsp;Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\r\n\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  Attribute Filters  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 05:28:34', '2017-10-02 05:28:34', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(489, 1, '2017-10-02 05:29:12', '2017-10-02 05:29:12', '[:en]Enforcer reports are designed for optimizing the deployment of traffic enforcers by focusing on the roads predicted to have the highest likelihood of traffic incidents. The reports take statistical predictions using location, time of day, day of week, and day of year, and then output a set number of locations.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-443 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Enforcer-Assignments.png\" width=\"770\" height=\"524\" />The reports are designed for printing and distribution at the beginning of a shift. An area for notes allows enforcer captains to include additional details for the shift and location.[:Ph]\r\nEnforcer reports are designed for optimizing the deployment of traffic enforcers by focusing on the roads predicted to have the highest likelihood of traffic incidents. The reports take statistical predictions using location, time of day, day of week, and day of year, and then output a set number of locations.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-443 size-full\" height=\"524\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Enforcer-Assignments.png\" width=\"770\">The reports are designed for printing and distribution at the beginning of a shift. An area for notes allows enforcer captains to include additional details for the shift and location.\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Enforcer Reports[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '279-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 05:29:12', '2017-10-02 05:29:12', '', 279, 'http://roadsafety.ph/279-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(490, 1, '2017-10-02 05:31:39', '2017-10-02 05:31:39', '\n\nDRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\n\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-roles-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\n\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\n\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 05:31:39', '2017-10-02 05:31:39', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
