(508, 1, '2017-10-02 06:30:40', '2017-10-02 06:30:40', '[:en]<p style=\"margin-top: -1px;\">DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.</p>\r\nWhile there are two <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a> on the DRIVER website (<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a> &amp; <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>), there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available: <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters.</a>\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used for the Map Interface.\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Types of Filters</span></h1>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></span></h3>\r\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-372 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01-1.png\" width=\"788\" height=\"196\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></span></h3>\r\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-373 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_02.png\" width=\"780\" height=\"194\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></span></h3>\r\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters.\r\n\r\nYou may save filters and access previously saved filters by clicking on the \"Saved Filters\" icon as shown below:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-375 size-full aligncenter\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_03.png\" width=\"805\" height=\"200\" />To clear filters or set filters back to their defaults, click the \"Clear Filters\" button\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-374 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_04.png\" width=\"792\" height=\"197\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]<p style=\"margin-top: -1px;\">DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.</p>\r\n\r\nWhile there are two <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a> on the DRIVER website (<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a> &amp; <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>), there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters.</a>\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used for the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Filters</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-372 size-full\" height=\"196\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01-1.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"788\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nSpatial Filters are tools that act as a geographic boundary filters. While there are two types of filters on the DRIVER website – Attribute Filters and Spatial Filters – Spatial Filters are used primarily for the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-373 size-full\" height=\"194\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_02.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"780\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nApplied filter sets can be saved for later use. The saved filters interface allows users to save and name the currently applied filters, and lists previously saved filters.\r\n\r\nYou may save filters and access previously saved filters by clicking on the \"Saved Filters\" icon as shown below:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-375 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"200\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_03.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"805\">To clear filters or set filters back to their defaults, click the \"Clear Filters\" button\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-374 size-full\" height=\"197\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_04.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"792\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Filtering & Searching', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '89-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 06:30:40', '2017-10-02 06:30:40', '', 89, 'http://roadsafety.ph/89-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(509, 1, '2017-10-02 06:31:47', '2017-10-02 06:31:47', '[:en]Unlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Native Layers</span></h1>\r\n<h3>Street View</h3>\r\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"588\" />\r\n<h3>Satelite View</h3>\r\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"535\" />\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span></h1>\r\n<h3>Incidents</h3>\r\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Incident data includes:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The date and time of the incident’s occurrence</li>\r\n 	<li>The location of the incident</li>\r\n 	<li>The time and date of when the incident was added to the DRIVER database</li>\r\n 	<li>Longitude &amp; Latitude</li>\r\n 	<li>Weather during the incident</li>\r\n 	<li>Light (if the incident occurred during the evening or the morning)</li>\r\n 	<li>Severity</li>\r\n 	<li>Collission Type</li>\r\n 	<li>Reporting Agency</li>\r\n 	<li>Location Approximate, and</li>\r\n 	<li>Additional details of the incident</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\r\n<h3>Interventions</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n<h3>Heatmap</h3>\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span>\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n<h3>Blackspots</h3>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n<h3>City/Province</h3>\r\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n<h3>Region</h3>\r\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Map)[:Ph]\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\r\n\r\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Incident data includes:\r\n\r\n<ul>  <li>  The date and time of the incident’s occurrence  </li>  <li>  The location of the incident  </li>  <li>  The time and date of when the incident was added to the DRIVER database  </li>  <li>  Longitude &amp; Latitude  </li>  <li>  Weather during the incident  </li>  <li>  Light (if the incident occurred during the evening or the morning)  </li>  <li>  Severity  </li>  <li>  Collission Type  </li>  <li>  Reporting Agency  </li>  <li>  Location Approximate, and  </li>  <li>  Additional details of the incident  </li>  </ul>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\r\n\r\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 06:31:47', '2017-10-02 06:31:47', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(510, 1, '2017-10-02 06:34:34', '2017-10-02 06:34:34', '\n\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text Search</span>\n\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Date Filter</span>\n\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Option Filter</span>\n\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.&nbsp;Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\n\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\n\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\n\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  </ul>', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 06:34:34', '2017-10-02 06:34:34', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(512, 1, '2017-10-02 06:38:37', '2017-10-02 06:38:37', '[:en]There are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></span></h3>\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Dashboard.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"636\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></span></h3>\r\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"638\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></span></h3>\r\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-318 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in, and includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full\" height=\"636\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Dashboard.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" height=\"638\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from a visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow for drawing geographic boundaries on the map using special drawing tools. Attribute Filters may be used alongside the Spatial Filters as well.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-318 size-full\" height=\"637\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'View Interfaces', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 06:38:37', '2017-10-02 06:38:37', '', 107, 'http://roadsafety.ph/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
