(530, 1, '2017-10-02 07:11:47', '2017-10-02 07:11:47', '[:en]<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-354 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map-1.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Map</span></h3>\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />Users may also zoom in and out of the map by clicking the (+) and (-) button on the leftmost side of the map, or may zoom in and out using a mouse.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-358 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Important Map Tools</span></h3>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-345 size-full\" style=\"width: 246px; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Layers_Only.png\" width=\"246\" height=\"475\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></h3>\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:  Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.  Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a></h3>\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-349 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"199\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></h3>\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-351 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\" height=\"291\" />The second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Hghlight_Graph_2.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"295\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-354 size-full\" height=\"637\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map-1.png\" width=\"1365\">The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">Users may also zoom in and out of the map by clicking the (+) and (-) button on the leftmost side of the map, or may zoom in and out using a mouse.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-358 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>  <div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-345 size-full\" height=\"475\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Layers_Only.png\" style=\"width: 246px; height: auto;\" width=\"246\">\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:&nbsp; Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.&nbsp; Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-349 size-full\" height=\"199\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-351 size-full\" height=\"291\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\">The second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full\" height=\"295\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Hghlight_Graph_2.png\" width=\"600\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Map Interface', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 07:11:47', '2017-10-02 07:11:47', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(531, 1, '2017-10-02 07:12:47', '2017-10-02 07:12:47', '[:en]<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to. The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.[:Ph]<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Region Default[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'region-default', '', '', '2017-10-02 17:12:32', '2017-10-02 17:12:32', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=531', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(532, 1, '2017-10-02 07:12:42', '2017-10-02 07:12:42', '[:en]DRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-roles-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a> may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a></h3>\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a> If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-roles-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 07:12:42', '2017-10-02 07:12:42', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
