(592, 1, '2017-10-02 11:11:14', '2017-10-02 11:11:14', '[:en]The Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page.\r\n\r\nOnce the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects “National Capital Region” in the Region Filter.\r\n\r\nThis filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-362 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe Region Filter filters allows the user to select a city, province, or region within the Attribute Filters located at a bar on top of the page.\r\n\r\nOnce the user selects their desired city, province, or region, the Region Filter will automatically zoom in on the map towards the area selected by the user.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, data is filtered to what is contained in that boundary. For example, incidents from Cebu would be filtered out if the user selects “National Capital Region” in the Region Filter.\r\n\r\nThis filter is applied on the map, record, and dashboard pages.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-362 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\"><h3>  Related Articles  </h3>[:]', '[:en]Region Filter[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '233-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 11:11:14', '2017-10-02 11:11:14', '', 233, 'http://roadsafety.ph/233-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(598, 1, '2017-10-02 11:48:37', '2017-10-02 11:48:37', '[:en]DRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-type-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a> may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a></h3>\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a> If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-roles-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 11:48:37', '2017-10-02 11:48:37', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
