(647, 1, '2017-10-02 14:16:56', '2017-10-02 14:16:56', '[:en]<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li>The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\" xlink=\"href\">Region Default</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]Application Defaults[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '455-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 14:16:56', '2017-10-02 14:16:56', '', 455, 'http://roadsafety.ph/455-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(649, 1, '2017-10-02 14:20:07', '2017-10-02 14:20:07', '[:en]The <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a> allows users to draw a custom boundary filter to narrow down incidents that occurred in the selected area.\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Types of Custom Area Filters</span></h1>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span></h3>\r\nThe Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using the Rectangular Tool</span></h3>\r\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\r\n\r\nOnce on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-390 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_03-Highlight-Tool.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />Once selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />Once the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-392 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Polygon Tool</span></h3>\r\nThe polygon tool allows the user to draw a more customized visual boundary on the map interface. Like the rectangular tool, the polygon tool will filter incidents and data in the selected area that the polygon was drawn on.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using the Polygon Tool</span></h3>\r\nTo start using the polygon tool, on the \"Polygon Tool\" button on the far left area of the map interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-396 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_03-Polygon-Tool_01-Select.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />On the map, select a point in the area you would like to start drawing on. Click once on your chosen point. This will activate the polygon tool. To delete a point in the polygon, simply again on click on the Polygon Tool button on the left side of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-397 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_04-Delete-Polygon-Tool.gif\" width=\"794\" height=\"440\" />\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\">Map Interface</a> allows users to draw a custom boundary filter to narrow down incidents that occurred in the selected area.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Types of Custom Area Filters</span>  </h1>  <h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Rectangular Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Rectangular Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\r\n\r\nOnce on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-390 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_03-Highlight-Tool.gif\" width=\"800\">Once selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" width=\"800\">Once the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-392 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up-1.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Polygon Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe polygon tool allows the user to draw a more customized visual boundary on the map interface. Like the rectangular tool, the polygon tool will filter incidents and data in the selected area that the polygon was drawn on.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Polygon Tool</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo start using the polygon tool, on the \"Polygon Tool\" button on the far left area of the map interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-396 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_03-Polygon-Tool_01-Select.png\" width=\"800\">On the map, select a point in the area you would like to start drawing on. Click once on your chosen point. This will activate the polygon tool. To delete a point in the polygon, simply again on click on the Polygon Tool button on the left side of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-397 size-full\" height=\"440\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_04-Delete-Polygon-Tool.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"794\">\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h1>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Custom Area Filter', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '126-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 14:20:07', '2017-10-02 14:20:07', '', 126, 'http://roadsafety.ph/126-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(650, 1, '2017-10-02 14:22:26', '2017-10-02 14:22:26', '[:en]The record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span></h3>\r\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span></h4>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text Search</span>\r\n\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Date Filter</span>\r\n\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Option Filter</span>\r\n\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons. Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\r\n\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe record list interface is simply a tabular view of what data is shown in the map interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nFrom the record view, users can view more details about an incident, or (depending on the type of user), edit the incident data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Record List</span>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">To access the record list, click on the “Dashboard” button on the topmost right corner of the website. A dropdown menu will appear, after which you may click the “Record List” button at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Tools in the Record List</span>  </h3>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 0px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Viewing Incident Data</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">On the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details window to appear, which shows more details of the incident data.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Filtering &amp; Searching</span>  </h4>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">The record list has a toolbar at the top of the page that allows the user access to the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which is the primary type of filter used in the Record List.</p>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 9px;\">On the Record List, the Attribute Filters allow users to narrow down incidents according to Name/Keyword, Date Range, Reporting Agency, Main Cause, and Severity.</p>  <p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Users may input any combination of these filters in order to further narrow down their search. Users may also opt to only input or apply one filter, or none at all.</p>  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 30px;\">  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Using Filters in the Record List</span>  </h4>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Text Search</span>\r\n\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSearching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Date Filter</span>\r\n\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nClicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Option Filter</span>\r\n\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.&nbsp;Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nMultiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">GIF HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Numeric Filters</span>\r\n\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters/\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Record List', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '70-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 14:22:26', '2017-10-02 14:22:26', '', 70, 'http://roadsafety.ph/70-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(651, 1, '2017-10-02 14:24:06', '2017-10-02 14:24:06', '[:en]Attribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\r\n\r\nThey can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list/\" xlink=\"href\">Record Lis</a>t or <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-372 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01-1.png\" width=\"813\" height=\"202\" />There are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Unlike the Map Interface, Attribute Filters are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\nNote how the Attribute Filters are available in the header bar on both the Map Interface (left), and Record List (right):\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-377 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Map.png\" width=\"395\" height=\"200\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" width=\"365\" height=\"185\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;\">Types of Attribute Filters</span></h1>\r\n<h3>Text Search</h3>\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-378 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_11-Filtering_By-Name.gif\" width=\"790\" height=\"438\" />Searching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n<h3>Date Filter</h3>\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-379 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_04-Filtering_Date-Range.gif\" width=\"777\" height=\"430\" />Clicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n<h3>Option Filter</h3>\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-380 size-full\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_05-Filtering_Reporting-Agency.gif\" width=\"813\" height=\"450\" />Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-381 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Blue_Reporting-Agency.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"48\" />\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Numeric Filter</span></h4>\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nAttribute Filters help the user narrow down their searches depending on the date of the incident, the reporting agency responsible, and the severity of the incident, among others.\r\n\r\nThey can be found on the topmost bar of the DRIVER website upon accessing either the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list/\">Record Lis</a>t or <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map/\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-372 size-full\" height=\"202\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01-1.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"813\">There are two ways to filter incidents on the DRIVER website: through the Record List, or the Map Interface. Unlike the Map Interface, Attribute Filters are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\nNote how the Attribute Filters are available in the header bar on both the Map Interface (left), and Record List (right):\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-377 size-full\" height=\"200\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Map.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"395\">\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" height=\"185\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"365\">\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-style:normal;font-weight:bold;\">Types of Attribute Filters</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Text Search  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Text Search filter can be found in the form of a search field on a bar at the top of both the Record List and the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-378 size-full\" height=\"438\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_11-Filtering_By-Name.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"790\">Searching in the text box will narrow down the incidents to ones that include the search term in a field marked as filterable/searchable in the database designer.\r\n\r\nTyping multiple words will perform a search for incidents that have both of the words in one or more fields.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Date Filter  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Date Filter can usually be found in between the Text Search Filter and the Option Filter, and narrows down incident data according to a date interval set by the user.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-379 size-full\" height=\"430\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_04-Filtering_Date-Range.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"777\">Clicking on the Date Filter launches a clickable interface to choose minimum and maximum dates for display and analysis. The default range of the Date Filter is the previous ninety days.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Option Filter  </h3>\r\n\r\nOption filters are shown in the form of enumeration fields (such as select lists and checkboxes), and are included as attribute filter dropdown buttons.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-380 size-full\" height=\"450\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_05-Filtering_Reporting-Agency.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"813\">Examples of option filters include Reporting Agency (concerned in the incident), Main Cause (of the incident), and Severity (of the incident).\r\n\r\nSelecting an option applies that filter to the data, and multiple options may be selected for any filter.\r\n\r\nActive filters are highlighted in light blue in the interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-381 size-full\" height=\"48\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Blue_Reporting-Agency.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h4>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Numeric Filter</span>  </h4>\r\n\r\nFields containing numbers may be filtered using a minimum/maximum range in the numeric filter.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters/\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters/\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Attribute Filters', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 14:24:06', '2017-10-02 14:24:06', '', 40, 'http://roadsafety.ph/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(652, 1, '2017-10-02 14:25:11', '2017-10-02 14:25:11', '[:en]<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-354 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map-1.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Map</span></h3>\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />Users may also zoom in and out of the map by clicking the (+) and (-) button on the leftmost side of the map, or may zoom in and out using a mouse.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-358 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Important Map Tools</span></h3>\r\nThere are several tools that can be accessed using the map. These tools allow the user to view data more efficiently by providing different ways to filter and access data.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a></h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"199\" />DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-345 size-full\" style=\"width: 246px; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Layers_Only.png\" width=\"246\" height=\"475\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></h3>\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:  Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.  Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></h3>\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-351 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\" height=\"291\" />The second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Hghlight_Graph_2.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"295\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-354 size-full\" height=\"637\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map-1.png\" width=\"1365\">The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">Users may also zoom in and out of the map by clicking the (+) and (-) button on the leftmost side of the map, or may zoom in and out using a mouse.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-358 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThere are several tools that can be accessed using the map. These tools allow the user to view data more efficiently by providing different ways to filter and access data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"199\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-345 size-full\" height=\"475\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Layers_Only.png\" style=\"width: 246px; height: auto;\" width=\"246\">\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:&nbsp; Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.&nbsp; Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-351 size-full\" height=\"291\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\">The second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full\" height=\"295\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Hghlight_Graph_2.png\" width=\"600\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]Map[:Ph]Map Interface[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 14:25:11', '2017-10-02 14:25:11', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
