(658, 1, '2017-10-02 14:44:06', '2017-10-02 14:44:06', '[:en]DRIVER has sets of tools to enable easier access for viewing, analyzing, and entering road incident data.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></h3>\r\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>.\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">All incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>. These two provide the user with the same information, but through two different visual interfaces.</p>\r\nThe <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a> is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></h3>\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.\r\n\r\nWhile the Record List &amp; Map Interface are the two View Interfaces on the DRIVER website, there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available: <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>.\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used to filter the Map Interface.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></h3>\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region.</span> Users may also choose between viewing the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/native-layers\" xlink=\"href\">Street View or the Satellite View</a>. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></h3>\r\nOn both the Dashboard and Map, users can view a list of available graphs and graph widgets which include aggregated data of recorded incidents on DRIVER. These graphs include a Time of Day, Day of Week aggregation of road incident occurrences, and  a total number of incidents over time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER has sets of tools to enable easier access for viewing, analyzing, and entering road incident data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>.\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">All incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>. These two provide the user with the same information, but through two different visual interfaces.</p>\r\n\r\nThe <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a> is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.\r\n\r\nWhile the&nbsp;Record List &amp; Map Interface are the two View Interfaces on the DRIVER website, there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available: <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>.\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used to filter the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\">Layers</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region.</span> Users may also choose between viewing the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/native-layers\">Street View or the Satellite View</a>. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nOn both the Dashboard and Map, users can view a list of available graphs and graph widgets which include aggregated data of recorded incidents on DRIVER. These graphs include a Time of Day, Day of Week aggregation of road incident occurrences, and&nbsp; a total number of incidents over time.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/reporting\">Reporting</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe DRIVER application includes functionality to generate custom reports from the database. These reports aggregate counts of incidents according to the rows and columns defined by users generating the reports. The reports also allow for geographic aggregation based on any uploaded boundary layers.\r\n\r\nCreating and editing reports for the DRIVER website is strictly for Analyst users only.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers\">Layers</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\">Graphs</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/reporting\">Reporting</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]DRIVER Tools[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '476-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 14:44:06', '2017-10-02 14:44:06', '', 476, 'http://roadsafety.ph/476-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
