(712, 1, '2017-10-02 15:48:52', '2017-10-02 15:48:52', '[:en]DRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a> may enter, edit, and export data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a></h3>\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a> If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-roles-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 15:48:52', '2017-10-02 15:48:52', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(713, 1, '2017-10-02 15:50:28', '2017-10-02 15:50:28', '[:en]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each “user type” or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/admin\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></span></h3>\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analyst</a></span></h3>\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></span></h3>\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-admin\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analyst</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (