(734, 1, '2017-10-02 16:32:19', '2017-10-02 16:32:19', '[:en]Unlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: <strong>Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region</strong>. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satellite View.\r\n\r\nUsers can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n<h3>Accessing Layers</h3>\r\nOn the map, layers can be accessed by selecting the Layer button on the top right side of the map, below the Saved Filters and Clear Filters button.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-637 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_08-Layers.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3>Types of Layers</h3>\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://roadsafety,ph/native-layers\" xlink=\"href\">Native Layers</a></h4>\r\n<strong>Street View</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"588\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Satellite View</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"535\" />\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<h4><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/geographic-boundary-layers\" xlink=\"href\">Geographic Boundary Layers</a></h4>\r\n<strong>Incidents</strong>\r\n\r\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Examples of Incident Data include (but are not limited to):\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The date and time of the incident’s occurrence</li>\r\n 	<li>When the incident was added to the DRIVER database</li>\r\n 	<li>The location of the incident</li>\r\n 	<li>Longitude &amp; Latitude</li>\r\n 	<li>Weather during the incident</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIncidents are marked with blue dots on the map.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-631 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Layers_Incidents.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"630\" />\r\n<h4></h4>\r\n<strong>Interventions</strong>\r\n\r\nLorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Donec ullamcorper luctus libero, consequat ornare libero consectetur a. Quisque at elit neque.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Heatmap</strong>\r\n\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area. They are represented by jet-type heatmap color schemes.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-632 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Layers_Heatmap.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1364\" height=\"636\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Blackspots</strong>\r\n\r\nBlack spots are sections of roadway or intersections that experience an unusually high number of traffic crashes. They are represented by broken red lines on the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-633 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Layers_Blackspots.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"634\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Region &amp; City/Province</strong>\r\n\r\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other. They are represented by red lines that form a boundary between cities and provinces.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-635 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Layers_City-Province.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"633\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSimilarly, the Region layer does the same, but is represented with green boundaries instead.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-636 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Layers_Region.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"634\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3>Using Filters with Layers</h3>\r\nDRIVER\'s filters may also be used alongside the layers. This can be done by simply choosing a layer, and then selecting a filter afterward to further narrow down the user\'s search.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-641 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_10-Layers-Filter-Severity.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/native-layers\" xlink=\"href\">Native Layers</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety,ph/geographic-boundary-layers\" xlink=\"href\">Geographic Boundary Layers</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;[:Ph]\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Native Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Street View  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Street View option shows the user a simple roadmap view of the Philippines, which is the default map view on the DRIVER Dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-336 size-full\" height=\"588\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Map.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  Satelite View  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe Satellite View option shows a pictured and more detailed view of the map, with data from OpenStreetMap.com. Users can switch between both the Satellite View and Street View by selecting the “Layers” option on the upper right corner of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-338 size-full\" height=\"535\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Zoom_Satellite.png\" width=\"1365\">\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Geographic Boundary Layers</span>  </h1>  <h3>  Incidents  </h3>\r\n\r\nThese are the incidents recorded into the DRIVER Website by Analyst users. Incident data includes:\r\n\r\n<ul>  <li>  The date and time of the incident’s occurrence  </li>  <li>  The location of the incident  </li>  <li>  The time and date of when the incident was added to the DRIVER database  </li>  <li>  Longitude &amp; Latitude  </li>  <li>  Weather during the incident  </li>  <li>  Light (if the incident occurred during the evening or the morning)  </li>  <li>  Severity  </li>  <li>  Collission Type  </li>  <li>  Reporting Agency  </li>  <li>  Location Approximate, and  </li>  <li>  Additional details of the incident  </li>  </ul>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Button)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Incident Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Interventions  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">(TO FOLLOW)</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Heatmap  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\r\n\r\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 16:32:19', '2017-10-02 16:32:19', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
