(748, 1, '2017-10-02 17:21:24', '2017-10-02 17:21:24', '[:en]Economic loss and societal harm costs are calculated based on an Ashlar configuration. Administrators choose an option-type field associated with the primary record type, such as “Severity”, and associate a cost with each of its values.\r\n\r\nIn the DRIVER interface, this cost is displayed both in the dashboard and map views.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-746 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screen-Shot-2017-10-03-at-1.12.46-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"936\" height=\"578\" />\r\nThe cost totals respect the geographic, temporal, and attribute filters applied in the map. This makes it possible for a user to associate an estimated cost for a search like <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">crashes involving pedestrians in a certain neighborhood in 2016.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-747 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screen-Shot-2017-10-03-at-1.14.26-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1518\" height=\"1184\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Since the Total Economic Loss and Societal Harm details varies constantly, the button on display on the map shows the total amount of loss or cost.</p>\r\nFilters may also be used alongside the Total Economic Loss &amp; Societal Harm. Any filters applied will automatically narrow down the cost of loss according to the filter set by the user.[:Ph]\r\nEconomic loss and societal harm costs are calculated based on an Ashlar configuration. Administrators choose an option-type field associated with the primary record type, such as “Severity”, and associate a cost with each of its values.\r\n\r\nIn the DRIVER interface, this cost is displayed both in the dashboard and map views. The cost totals respect the geographic, temporal, and attribute filters applied in the map. This makes it possible for a user to associate an estimated cost for a search like <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">crashes involving pedestrians in a certain neighborhood in 2016.</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Since the Total Economic Loss and Societal Harm details varies constantly, the button on display on the map shows the total amount of loss or cost.</p>\r\n\r\nFilters may also be used alongside the Total Economic Loss &amp; Societal Harm. Any filters applied will automatically narrow down the cost of loss according to the filter set by the user.\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Cost to Society[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '281-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 17:21:24', '2017-10-02 17:21:24', '', 281, 'http://roadsafety.ph/281-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(749, 1, '2017-10-02 18:13:12', '2017-10-02 18:13:12', '[:en]DRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a> may enter, edit, and export data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a></h3>\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a> If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is website designed to view, collect, and analyze data about road incidents that occur at a particular place in the Philippines. These include traffic incidents and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-roles-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-permissions\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved in the accident, etc). <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nTo access DRIVER, go to <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they can click on the “Log in with provider’” button.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 18:13:12', '2017-10-02 18:13:12', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
