(754, 1, '2017-10-02 18:20:22', '2017-10-02 18:20:22', '[:en]DRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines, particularly traffic incidents, disruptions, and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a></h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a> may enter, edit, and export data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a></h3>\r\nThe DRIVER website can be accessed through <a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a> If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they may enter the domain by clicking on the “Log in with Google’” button, and select their user.\r\n\r\nIf needed, admin users may also grant login access to other user types by providing other users with their own login details.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines, particularly traffic incidents, disruptions, and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data.</p>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe DRIVER website can be accessed through&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they may enter the domain by clicking on the “Log in with Google’” button, and select their user.\r\n\r\nIf needed, admin users may also grant login access to other user types by providing other users with their own login details.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 18:20:22', '2017-10-02 18:20:22', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(755, 1, '2017-10-02 18:25:51', '2017-10-02 18:25:51', '[:en]DRIVER has sets of tools to enable easier access for viewing, analyzing, and entering road incident data.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></h3>\r\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>.\r\n\r\nThe <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a> is the user\'s default view after logging in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">On the other hand, detailed incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>. These two provide the user with the same information, but through two different visual interfaces. The Record List is simply a tabular view of all recorded incidents in the DRIVER website, while the Map allows users a visual representation of incidents and road occurrences.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></h3>\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may be used alongside different tools found on DRIVER, such as Layers, Graphs, and more.\r\n\r\nWhile the Record List &amp; Map Interface are the two View Interfaces on the DRIVER website, there are also two main types of filtering &amp; searching features available: <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>.\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used to filter the Map Interface.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></h3>\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/native-layers\" xlink=\"href\">Street View or the Satellite View</a>. They may also choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></h3>\r\nOn both the Dashboard and Map, users can view a list of available graphs and graph widgets which include aggregated data of recorded incidents on DRIVER. These graphs include a Time of Day, Day of Week aggregation of road incident occurrences, and  a total number of incidents over time.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER has sets of tools to enable easier access for viewing, analyzing, and entering road incident data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThere are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>.\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">All incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">Record List</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\">Map</a>. These two provide the user with the same information, but through two different visual interfaces.</p>\r\n\r\nThe <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\">Dashboard</a> is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nDRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database.\r\n\r\nWhile the&nbsp;Record List &amp; Map Interface are the two View Interfaces on the DRIVER website, there are also two types of filtering &amp; searching features available: <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\">Attribute Filters</a> and <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\">Spatial Filters</a>.\r\n\r\nAttribute Filters are the different types of filters that are used for both the Record List and the Map Interface of the DRIVER website, while Spatial Filters are primarily used to filter the Map Interface.\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\">Layers</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access: Incidents, Interventions, <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region.</span> Users may also choose between viewing the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/native-layers\">Street View or the Satellite View</a>. Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nOn both the Dashboard and Map, users can view a list of available graphs and graph widgets which include aggregated data of recorded incidents on DRIVER. These graphs include a Time of Day, Day of Week aggregation of road incident occurrences, and&nbsp; a total number of incidents over time.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/reporting\">Reporting</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe DRIVER application includes functionality to generate custom reports from the database. These reports aggregate counts of incidents according to the rows and columns defined by users generating the reports. The reports also allow for geographic aggregation based on any uploaded boundary layers.\r\n\r\nCreating and editing reports for the DRIVER website is strictly for Analyst users only.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers\">Layers</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\">Graphs</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/reporting\">Reporting</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]DRIVER Tools[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '476-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-02 18:25:51', '2017-10-02 18:25:51', '', 476, 'http://roadsafety.ph/476-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(756, 1, '2017-10-02 18:28:16', '2017-10-02 18:28:16', '[:en]There are three ways that a user can view and access data on the DRIVER website: Through the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>, or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map Interface</a>.\r\n\r\nAll incidents recorded in DRIVER can be accessed through the record list view and the map view; the dashboard is the default view after the user logs in, and provides a summary of incidents of DRIVER’s data within a specific period of time.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard/\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a></h3>\r\nAside from acting as the home screen of the site, the dashboard also includes application defaults that allow the user to access an overview of information about the data in DRIVER.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Dashboard.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"636\" />\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></h3>\r\nThe record list is simply a collection of all incidents recorded on the DRIVER website, shown in tabular form. Incidents in this view may be filtered using <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>, which help the user narrow down their searches to dates, reporting agency, and severity, among others.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-319 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Record-List.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"638\" />\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></h3>\r\nAside from a more general, visual representation of where the incidents occurred, the map interface also provides the user with filters called <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>, that allow