(792, 1, '2017-10-03 08:49:55', '2017-10-03 08:49:55', '[:en]The dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website.\r\n<h3>How to Access the Dashboard</h3>\r\nThe dashboard is automatically accessible directly after logging in into the main DRIVER site.\r\n<h3>Widgets Available in the Dashboard</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\nDRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li>The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Filtering Widgets in the Dashboard</h3>\r\nThe data within the dashboard widgets can be further narrowed down by using the filters available in the header bar seen directly above the dashboard.\r\n\r\nFor example,take the default view of the dashboard, which displays data from across all incidents in the Philippines:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-795 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_DASHBOARD_Before_Filter.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"636\" />\r\n\r\nHowever, upon applying the City/Province Filter on the header bar above, the dashboard data is automatically filtered based on the chosen City/Province filter set by the user. This is what the dashboard looks like after setting the filter to Metro Manila:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-797 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_DASHBOARD_After_Filter.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"639\" />\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Dashboard_2[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'dashboard_2', '', '', '2017-10-03 09:09:05', '2017-10-03 09:09:05', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=792', 0, 'post', '', 0),
