(822, 1, '2017-10-03 10:59:34', '2017-10-03 10:59:34', '[:en]Users can view Incident Reports and Locations through a variety of ways.\r\n<h3>Viewing Individual Incident Reports</h3>\r\nIndividual incident reports may also be accessed through a section of the DRIVER website called the Record List. The Record List is simply a tabular view of all incidents recorded in DRIVER. Each entry in the record list may be selected to view more details of the road incident, such as the time and date, or severity of the incident\'s occurrence.\r\n\r\nTo view through the record list, click on the \"Dashboard\" button located on the top left corner of the dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOn the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”. Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details popup to appear, which shows users more details of the incident data.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-809 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/02_Record-List_02-Filtering_View-Incident.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Volume</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Viewing Number of Incidents</h3>\r\nUsers can view the total number of incidents on the Incident widget on the dashboard:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-797 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_DASHBOARD_After_Filter.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"639\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-817 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Screenshot_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"352\" height=\"168\" />[:]', '[:en]Incident Reports & Locations[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '807-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 10:59:34', '2017-10-03 10:59:34', '', 807, 'http://roadsafety.ph/807-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(823, 1, '2017-10-03 11:01:45', '2017-10-03 11:01:45', '[:en]Users can view Incident Reports and Locations through a variety of ways.\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Geographic Area</h3>\r\nDRIVER has a Map interface, which is a visual representation of all incidents recorded within the DRIVER website. To view incidents by geographic area, the user must first access the Map.\r\n\r\nTo access the map, click on the \"Dashboard\" dropdown on the top left corner of the page, and click on \"Map.\" This will automatically take you to DRIVER\'s main Map interface.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-811 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nIncidents on the map are marked by a blue dot that represents where road incident occurred. Clicking on these dots will prompt a small popup to open, which will contain a short summary of the selected incident\'s details.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-358 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n\r\nFrom this popup, users may also view more details of the road incident by clicking on the \"View\" button inside it. This will prompt a larger popup to open, which will contain a more detailed account of the selected road incident.\r\n<h3>Viewing Individual Incident Reports</h3>\r\nIndividual incident reports may also be accessed through a section of the DRIVER website called the Record List. The Record List is simply a tabular view of all incidents recorded in DRIVER. Each entry in the record list may be selected to view more details of the road incident, such as the time and date, or severity of the incident\'s occurrence.\r\n\r\nTo view through the record list, click on the \"Dashboard\" button located on the top left corner of the dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOn the right-most side of each entry in the list of incidents, you will find a button that says “View”. Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details popup to appear, which shows users more details of the incident data.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-809 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/02_Record-List_02-Filtering_View-Incident.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Volume</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Viewing Number of Incidents</h3>\r\nUsers can view the total number of incidents on the Incident widget on the dashboard:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-797 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_DASHBOARD_After_Filter.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"639\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-817 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Screenshot_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"352\" height=\"168\" />[:]', '[:en]Incident Reports & Locations[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '807-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 11:01:45', '2017-10-03 11:01:45', '', 807, 'http://roadsafety.ph/807-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
