 </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]Exporting Data[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 12:12:45', '2017-10-03 12:12:45', '', 213, 'http://roadsafety.ph/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(834, 1, '2017-10-03 12:15:55', '2017-10-03 12:15:55', '[:en]For analysis outside of the system, data may be exported as a set of CSV files.\r\n\r\n<strong>How to Export</strong>\r\n\r\nTo export data, go to the Map interface. On the bottom left of the Map, select the \"Export Data\" tab, and click \"Export CSV\".\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">SCREENSHOTS</span>\r\n\r\nDRIVER data is stored in a relational database that supports many-to-one relationships. This means that for a given incident, there may be many people and vehicles involved.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">View Incidents</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nData in the map may be exported as a set of CSV files.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOTS</span>\r\n\r\nDRIVER data is stored in a relational database that supports many-to-one relationships. This means that for a given incident, there may be many people and vehicles involved.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOTS</span>\r\n\r\nThe export CSV zip file contains a CSV for each type of related object, linked to the primary accident table via a unique ID.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOTS</span>\r\n\r\nThe CSV files also contain the latitude and longitude for the incident location. These files may be further analyzed using spreadsheet or database software.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Related Articles</span>  </h1>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\">View Incidents</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]Exporting Data[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 12:15:55', '2017-10-03 12:15:55', '', 213, 'http://roadsafety.ph/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(845, 1, '2017-10-03 12:57:50', '2017-10-03 12:57:50', '[:en]The dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. It includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Widgets on the Dashboard</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\nDRIVER gives users a set of widgets available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span></li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Filtering Dashboard Data According to Area</h3>\r\nThese dashboard widgets may also be filtered according to the a particular region, city, or province set by the user. To do this, simply click on the tab that says \"Regions\" on the header bar to select whether you would like to filter the dashboard data according to region, or city/province.\r\n\r\nThe \"All\" button (next to the \"Regions\" button on the header bar) is a dropdown that lets users select a region, city, or province. The \"All\" button\'s contents will adjust depending on whether the user selects \"Region\" or \"City/Province\" in the dropdown.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></h3>\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map</a> or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Related Articles</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\" xlink=\"href\">Application Defaults</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map</a>&nbsp;or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 12:57:50', '2017-10-03 12:57:50', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(846, 1, '2017-10-03 12:58:18', '2017-10-03 12:58:18', '[:en]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each “user type” or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">Admin</h3>\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n<h3>Analyst</h3>\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n<h3>Public Viewer</h3>\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.[:Ph]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each “user type” or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></span></h3>\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analyst</a></span></h3>\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></span></h3>\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/getting-started/\" xlink=\"href\">Getting Started</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-admin\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analyst</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:]', 'User Types & Roles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 12:58:18', '2017-10-03 12:58:18', '', 95, 'http://roadsafety.ph/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(847, 1, '2017-10-03 13:00:35', '2017-10-03 13:00:35', '[:en]The dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. It includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Widgets on the Dashboard</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\nDRIVER gives users a set of widgets available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span></li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Filtering Dashboard Data According to Area</h3>\r\nThese dashboard widgets may also be filtered according to the a particular region, city, or province set by the user. To do this, simply click on the tab that says \"Regions\" on the header bar to select whether you would like to filter the dashboard data according to region, or city/province.\r\n\r\nThe \"All\" button (next to the \"Regions\" button on the header bar) is a dropdown that lets users select a region, city, or province. The \"All\" button\'s contents will adjust depending on whether the user selects \"Region\" or \"City/Province\" in the dropdown.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n<h3>Map &amp; Record List</h3>\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the Map or the Record List.\r\n\r\nBoth can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nAccessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Related Articles</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\" xlink=\"href\">Application Defaults</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map</a>&nbsp;or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 13:00:35', '2017-10-03 13:00:35', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
