 for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map</a>&nbsp;or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 13:31:30', '2017-10-03 13:31:30', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(849, 1, '2017-10-03 13:32:35', '2017-10-03 13:32:35', '[:en]DRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines, particularly traffic incidents, disruptions, and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3>User Types &amp; Roles</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different types of users on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">Public Viewers may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">Analysts may enter, edit, and export data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">Administrator<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">s</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Accessing DRIVER</h3>\r\nThe DRIVER website can be accessed through http://roadsafety.gov.ph. If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they may enter the domain by clicking on the “Log in with Google’” button, and select their user.\r\n\r\nIf needed, admin users may also grant login access to other user types by providing other users with their own login details.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines, particularly traffic incidents, disruptions, and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data.</p>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe DRIVER website can be accessed through&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they may enter the domain by clicking on the “Log in with Google’” button, and select their user.\r\n\r\nIf needed, admin users may also grant login access to other user types by providing other users with their own login details.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 13:32:35', '2017-10-03 13:32:35', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(850, 1, '2017-10-03 13:48:49', '2017-10-03 13:48:49', '[:en]Users can view and filter Incident Reports and their locations through a variety of ways on DRIVER.\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Geographic Area</h3>\r\nTo view incidents by geographic area, the user must first access the Map. To do this, click on the \"Dashboard\" dropdown on the top left corner of the page, and click on \"Map.\"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-811 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nIncidents on the map are marked by blue dots. Clicking on these dots will prompt a small popup to open, which contains a short summary of the selected incident\'s details. Users may also zoom in and out of the map using either a mouse/trackpad, or the zoom buttons on the left most side of the page.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-358 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n\r\nFrom this popup, users may also view more details of the road incident by clicking on the \"View\" button inside it. This will prompt a larger popup to open, which will contain a more detailed account of the selected road incident.\r\n<h3>Viewing Individual Incident Reports</h3>\r\nThe Record List is simply a tabular view of all incidents recorded in DRIVER. Each entry in the record list may be selected to view more details of the road incident, such as the time and date of its occurrence, the main cause, and severity.\r\n\r\nTo start, click on the \"Dashboard\" button located on the top left corner of the dashboard. This will prompt a dropdown to appear, after which you may click the \"Record List\" button.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nIn each of entry within the Record List, you will find a button that says “View” on the rightmost side of the entry Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details popup to appear. This will show more details of each individual incident.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-809 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/02_Record-List_02-Filtering_View-Incident.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Volume</h3>\r\nIncidents can also be viewed by volume of severity through the Heat Map and Blackspots. The Heat Map shows\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Viewing Number of Incidents</h3>\r\nUsers can also view the total number of incidents on the Incident widget on the dashboard:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-797 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_DASHBOARD_After_Filter.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"639\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-817 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Screenshot_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"352\" height=\"168\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Incident Reports & Locations[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '807-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 13:48:49', '2017-10-03 13:48:49', '', 807, 'http://roadsafety.ph/807-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(851, 1, '2017-10-03 13:51:30', '2017-10-03 13:51:30', '[:en]<h3>Viewing Incidents by Road Vulnerability</h3>\r\nBlack spots are sections of roadway or intersections that experience an unusually high number of traffic\r\ncrashes.\r\n\r\nTo view the black spots of a particular area, go to the Map interface of the page, select the layers button, and tick \"Black Spots.\"\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Severity</h3>\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\r\n\r\nTo use the heatmap go to the Map, select the layers button, and tick \"Heat map\".\r\n\r\nThe heat map and black spots may also be used together with other filters on the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Vulnerabiltiy of Roads to Crashes[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '827-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 13:51:30', '2017-10-03 13:51:30', '', 827, 'http://roadsafety.ph/827-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(852, 1, '2017-10-03 13:56:09', '2017-10-03 13:56:09', '[:en]Users can view and filter Incident Reports and their locations through a variety of ways on DRIVER.\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Geographic Area</h3>\r\nTo view incidents by geographic area, the user must first access the Map. To do this, click on the \"Dashboard\" dropdown on the top left corner of the page, and click on \"Map.\"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-811 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nIncidents on the map are marked by blue dots. Clicking on these dots will prompt a small popup to open, which contains a short summary of the selected incident\'s details. Users may also zoom in and out of the map using either a mouse/trackpad, or the zoom buttons on the left most side of the page.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-358 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n\r\nFrom this popup, users may also view more details of the road incident by clicking on the \"View\" button inside it. This will prompt a larger popup to open, which will contain a more detailed account of the selected road incident.\r\n<h3>Viewing Individual Incident Reports</h3>\r\nThe Record List is simply a tabular view of all incidents recorded in DRIVER. Each entry in the record list may be selected to view more details of the road incident, such as the time and date of its occurrence, the main cause, and severity.\r\n\r\nTo start, click on the \"Dashboard\" button located on the top left corner of the dashboard. This will prompt a dropdown to appear, after which you may click the \"Record List\" button.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nIn each of entry within the Record List, you will find a button that says “View” on the rightmost side of the entry Clicking on this will prompt the Incident Details popup to appear. This will show more details of each individual incident.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-809 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/02_Record-List_02-Filtering_View-Incident.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Volume</h3>\r\nIncidents can also be viewed by volume of severity through the Heat Map and Blackspots. The Heat Map shows the volume of the severity of a particular area. Incidents can be filtered according to volume of severity by clicking on the Layer button on the right most corner of the map, and ticking on \"Heat map.\"\r\n\r\nBlackspots on the other hand, shows the volume of severity of road vulnerability in respect to crashes. To view incidents by blackspots,  click on the Layer button on the right most corner of the map, and tick \"Blackspots.\"\r\n<h3>Viewing Number of Incidents</h3>\r\nUsers can also view the total number of incidents on the Incident widget on the dashboard:\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-797 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_DASHBOARD_After_Filter.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"639\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-817 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Screenshot_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"352\" height=\"168\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Incident Reports & Locations[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '807-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 13:56:09', '2017-10-03 13:56:09', '', 807, 'http://roadsafety.ph/807-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(853, 1, '2017-10-03 15:37:53', '2017-10-03 15:37:53', '[:en]The dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. It includes summary and overview information about the data within the DRIVER website.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Dashboard Widgets</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\nDRIVER gives users a set of widgets on the dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>A widget displaying the total economic loss and societal harm from the incidents over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>A widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span></li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Filtering Dashboard Data by Area</h3>\r\nThese dashboard widgets may also be filtered according to the a particular region, city, or province set by the user.\r\n\r\nTo do this, simply click on the \"Regions\" tab on the header bar towards the upper left of the dashboard. From here, select whether you would like to filter the dashboard data according to region, or city/province.\r\n\r\nThe \"All\" button (next to the \"Regions\" tab) is a dropdown that lets users select a region, city, or province. The \"All\" button\'s contents will adjust depending on whether the user selects \"Region\" or \"City/Province\" in the dropdown.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n<h3>Accessing Incident Data from the Dashboard</h3>\r\nOn the dashboard, users can also access and further filter data through the Map or the Record List.\r\n\r\nThe Map lets users view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more.\r\n\r\nThe Record List is a collection of all incidents reported in driver. Users may also narrow down their searches on the record list using filters.\r\n\r\nBoth the Map and the Record List can be accessed through the \"Dashboard\" button/dropdown located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard. From here, users may select whether they would like to access the Record List or the Map.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nTo access the Record List, click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h3><strong>Related Articles</strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\" xlink=\"href\">Application Defaults</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map</a>&nbsp;or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 15:37:53', '2017-10-03 15:37:53', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
