"text-decoration:underline;font-weight:bold;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  Blackspots  </h3>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Button)</span><br><span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)</span>\r\n\r\n<h3>  City/Province  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe City/Province layer shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n<h3>  Region  </h3>\r\n\r\nAs with the City/Province layer, the Region layer also shows a visual boundary that segregates provinces from each other.\r\n\r\nSCREENSHOT HERE (Button)<br>SCREENSHOT HERE (Map)\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Layers[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '193-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 16:59:09', '2017-10-03 16:59:09', '', 193, 'http://roadsafety.ph/193-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(867, 1, '2017-10-03 17:01:40', '2017-10-03 17:01:40', '\n\nGraphs on DRIVER can be accessed by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" height=\"341\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\">There are two types of graphs: One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\n\nThe second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\n\nUsers may toggle between these two graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\n\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter wp-image-628 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_Map_06-Graph-Toggle.gif\" width=\"800\">Applying a filter or (set of filters) also determines the data shown in the graph. Note how the graph changes as the user sets a different filter.\n\n<img alt class=\"aligncenter wp-image-629 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_Map_07-Graph-Filter.gif\" width=\"800\">\n\n', '[:en]Graphs[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '553-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:01:40', '2017-10-03 17:01:40', '', 553, 'http://roadsafety.ph/553-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(868, 1, '2017-10-03 17:02:18', '2017-10-03 17:02:18', '[:en]DRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines, particularly traffic incidents, disruptions, and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n<h3>User Types &amp; Roles</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different types of users on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">Public Viewers may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">Analysts may enter, edit, and export data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">Administrator<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">s</a> have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Accessing DRIVER</h3>\r\nThe DRIVER website can be accessed through http://roadsafety.gov.ph. If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they may enter the domain by clicking on the “Log in with Google’” button, and select their user.\r\n\r\nIf needed, admin users may also grant login access to other user types by providing other users with their own login details.[:Ph]\r\nDRIVER is designed to view, collect, and analyze road incident data in the Philippines, particularly traffic incidents, disruptions, and crimes. The application provides data viewing and entry tools, graph and map interfaces, custom report and filter tools, multiple concurrent user editing, and data exports.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a>  </h3>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\">There are different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-roles\" xlink=\"href\">types of users</a> on the DRIVER website, each with a designated role. <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewers</a> may view data on DRIVER, but with limitations (i.e. they may not access plate numbers, names of persons involved incidents, etc).</p>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analysts</a>&nbsp;may enter, edit, and export data.</p>  <p style=\"margin-top: -2px;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Administrators</a>&nbsp;have login capabilities to the database and design editor of the software, and can modify the structure of the database.</p>  <h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing DRIVER</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThe DRIVER website can be accessed through&nbsp;<a href=\"http://roadsafety.gov.ph.\" xlink=\"href\">http://roadsafety.gov.ph.</a>&nbsp;If a user has an account with a supported provider (e.g. Google), they may enter the domain by clicking on the “Log in with Google’” button, and select their user.\r\n\r\nIf needed, admin users may also grant login access to other user types by providing other users with their own login details.\r\n\r\n<h3>  Related Articles  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/accessing-driver\" xlink=\"href\">Accessing Driver</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://user-types-and-permissions\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Permissions</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Important Tools on DRIVER</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Explore the Dashboard</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]About DRIVER[:Ph]Tungkol sa DRIVER[:tl]Getting Started[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:02:18', '2017-10-03 17:02:18', '', 172, 'http://roadsafety.ph/172-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(869, 1, '2017-10-03 17:04:54', '2017-10-03 17:04:54', '[:en]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each “user type” or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\">Admin</h3>\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software.\r\n\r\nAdmins can also modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n<h3>Analyst</h3>\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n\r\nUsers may request for Analyst access by contacting an Admin user.\r\n<h3>Public Viewer</h3>\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data or view person or vehicle information.[:Ph]There are three roles with differing permissions in DRIVER: the (1) Admin, (2) Analyst, and (3) Public Viewer. Each “user type” or role provides different levels of functionality, and some have limited access to certain parts of DRIVER.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></span></h3>\r\nThe admin role has access to the most functionality in the application, including login capability to the database design editor software. Admins can modify the structure of the database, add new fields, make fields required, upload geographic boundaries, and manage users. The database design editor software will be covered in a separate user manual. In DRIVER, admins may export user access logs for analysis.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analyst</a></span></h3>\r\nThe analyst role includes permissions to view and edit all data in DRIVER. Analysts may add, edit, and delete incidents and interventions, and have access to all event information, including details associated with an incident such as people and vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></span></h3>\r\nPublic users may register to view basic incident data. They may not edit any data, and can not view person or vehicle information.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Related Articles</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/2017/09/26/getting-started/\" xlink=\"href\">Getting Started</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-admin\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-analyst\" xlink=\"href\">Analyst</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/driver-public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:]', 'User Types & Roles', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:04:54', '2017-10-03 17:04:54', '', 95, 'http://roadsafety.ph/95-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
