(870, 1, '2017-10-03 17:05:23', '2017-10-03 17:05:23', '[:en]The dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. It includes summary and overview information about the data within the DRIVER website.\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Dashboard Widgets</span></h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\nDRIVER gives users a set of widgets on the dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity</li>\r\n 	<li>An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks</li>\r\n 	<li>A widget displaying the total economic loss and societal harm from the incidents over the last 90 days</li>\r\n 	<li>A widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.</li>\r\n 	<li><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span></li>\r\n 	<li>A list of the user’s saved filters, if any.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Filtering Dashboard Data by Area</h3>\r\nThese dashboard widgets may also be filtered according to the a particular region, city, or province set by the user.\r\n\r\nTo do this, simply click on the \"Regions\" tab on the header bar towards the upper left of the dashboard. From here, select whether you would like to filter the dashboard data according to region, or city/province.\r\n\r\nThe \"All\" button (next to the \"Regions\" tab) is a dropdown that lets users select a region, city, or province. The \"All\" button\'s contents will adjust depending on whether the user selects \"Region\" or \"City/Province\" in the dropdown.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"441\" />\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n<h3>Accessing Incident Data from the Dashboard</h3>\r\nOn the dashboard, users can also access and further filter data through the Map or the Record List.\r\n\r\nThe Map lets users view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more.\r\n\r\nThe Record List is a collection of all incidents reported in driver. Users may also narrow down their searches on the record list using filters.\r\n\r\nBoth the Map and the Record List can be accessed through the \"Dashboard\" button/dropdown located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard. From here, users may select whether they would like to access the Record List or the Map.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nTo access the Record List, click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />[:Ph]\r\nThe dashboard interface is the default view after logging in. This interface includes summary and overview information about the data in the DRIVER website. Different <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">Viewing Interfaces</a> can be accessed through the Dashboard as well.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/application-defaults\" xlink=\"href\">Application Defaults</a></span>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-360 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Numbered-Dashboard.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER gives users a set of application defaults available through the Dashboard that allow for both easier viewing and filtering. These are:\r\n\r\n<ol>  <li>  An incident map that shows accidents that occurred over the past two weeks  </li>  <li>  Another map that shows current black spots color coded according to severity  </li>  <li>  A statistics widget that displays statistics of total economic loss and societal harm over the last 90 days  </li>  <li>  Another widget that displays the total number of incidents that occurred during the past 30, 60, and 90 days.  </li>  <li>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">The ToDDoW (Time of Day, Day of Week) Chart, which shows the concentration of incidents over the last 90 days, and;</span>  </li>  <li>  A list of the user’s saved filters, if any  </li>  </ol>\r\n\r\nThese Application Defaults may be filtered according to the Region Default set by the user.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/region-default\">Region Default</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-362 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Region-Default.png\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-361 size-full\" height=\"441\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Province-Default.png\" width=\"800\">A header bar on the Dashboard allows users to set a default city, province, or region, which when selected, the Dashboard’s Application Defaults will automatically adjust to.&nbsp;The region chosen will filter the maps, ToDDoW chart, and widgets to provide data for incidents that occurred only within that geographic boundary.\r\n\r\nThis default setting is preserved between user sessions on the same computer.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nAside from the Dashboard, users can view, access, and filter data through either the<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\"> Map</a>&nbsp;or the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>. Both can be accessed through a dropdown menu located on the leftmost part of the header bar of the Dashboard.\r\n\r\nTo access the Map, simply go to the “Dashboard” button and select “Map” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-363 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard-1.gif\" width=\"800\">Accessing the Record List requires a similar process: click on the “Dashboard” button, and select “Record List” from the dropdown menu.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-364 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/02_Record-List_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <strong>Related Articles</strong>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces/\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map\" xlink=\"href\">Map</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/record-list\" xlink=\"href\">Record List</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filtering &amp; Searching</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', 'Dashboard', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '18-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:05:23', '2017-10-03 17:05:23', '', 18, 'http://roadsafety.ph/18-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(871, 1, '2017-10-03 17:05:47', '2017-10-03 17:05:47', '[:en]Economic loss and societal harm costs are calculated based on an Ashlar configuration. Administrators choose an option-type field associated with the primary record type, such as “Severity”, and associate a cost with each of its values.\r\n\r\nIn the DRIVER interface, this cost is displayed both in the dashboard and map views.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-746 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screen-Shot-2017-10-03-at-1.12.46-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"936\" height=\"578\" />\r\nThe cost totals respect the geographic, temporal, and attribute filters applied in the map. This makes it possible for a user to associate an estimated cost for a search like <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">crashes involving pedestrians in a certain neighborhood in 2016.</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-747 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screen-Shot-2017-10-03-at-1.14.26-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1518\" height=\"1184\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Since the Total Economic Loss and Societal Harm details varies constantly, the button on display on the map shows the total amount of loss or cost.</p>\r\nFilters may also be used alongside the Total Economic Loss &amp; Societal Harm. Any filters applied will automatically narrow down the cost of loss according to the filter set by the user.[:Ph]\r\nEconomic loss and societal harm costs are calculated based on an Ashlar configuration. Administrators choose an option-type field associated with the primary record type, such as “Severity”, and associate a cost with each of its values.\r\n\r\nIn the DRIVER interface, this cost is displayed both in the dashboard and map views. The cost totals respect the geographic, temporal, and attribute filters applied in the map. This makes it possible for a user to associate an estimated cost for a search like <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">crashes involving pedestrians in a certain neighborhood in 2016.</span>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\">Since the Total Economic Loss and Societal Harm details varies constantly, the button on display on the map shows the total amount of loss or cost.</p>\r\n\r\nFilters may also be used alongside the Total Economic Loss &amp; Societal Harm. Any filters applied will automatically narrow down the cost of loss according to the filter set by the user.\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Cost to Society[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '281-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:05:47', '2017-10-03 17:05:47', '', 281, 'http://roadsafety.ph/281-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(872, 1, '2017-10-03 17:06:34', '2017-10-03 17:06:34', '[:en]<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/cost-to-society/\" xlink=\"href\">View Cost to Society</a>\r\n\r\n<a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/incident-reports\" xlink=\"href\">Incident Reports</a>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Incidents by Geographic Area</li>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Individual Incident Reports</li>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Incidents by Volume of Severity</li>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Total Number of Incidents</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/road-vulnerability\" xlink=\"href\">Road Vulnerability</a>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Road Vulnerability in Relation to Incidents</li>\r\n 	<li>Viewing Incidents by Severity</li>\r\n</ul>[:]', '[:en]View Data[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '474-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:06:34', '2017-10-03 17:06:34', '', 474, 'http://roadsafety.ph/474-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(873, 1, '2017-10-03 17:07:01', '2017-10-03 17:07:01', '[:en]<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-354 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map-1.png\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n<h3>How to Access the Map</h3>\r\nWhile there are small map widgets available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nUsers may zoom in and out of the map by clicking the (+) and (-) button on the leftmost side of the map, or may zoom in and out using a trackpad or mouse.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-358 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/map-tools\" xlink=\"href\">Tools in the Map Interface</a></h3>\r\nThere are several tools that can be accessed using the map. These tools allow the user to view data more efficiently by providing different ways to filter and access data.\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a></h3>\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 size-full aligncenter\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01.png\" width=\"800\" height=\"199\" />DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc.\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-345 size-full\" style=\"width: 246px; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Layers_Only.png\" width=\"246\" height=\"475\" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a></h3>\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:  Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.  Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\">\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a></h3>\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-628 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/01_Map_06-Graph-Toggle.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-351 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\" height=\"291\" />The second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Hghlight_Graph_2.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"295\" />\r\n<h3><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-354 size-full\" height=\"637\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Screenshot_Map-1.png\" width=\"1365\">The map interface is one of the principal tools in the DRIVER application, and is used to view incidents in a variety of ways, such as through filter tools, layers, and more. Depending on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types\" xlink=\"href\">type of user</a>, the Map also grants access to interventions, additional graphs, custom report builder tools, and data exports, among others.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How to Access the Map</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nWhile there are small map sections available on the <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/dashboard\" xlink=\"href\">Dashboard</a>, the main Map interface can be accessed by clicking on the the “Dashboard” drop down on the topmost left bar on the DRIVER dashboard.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">Users may also zoom in and out of the map by clicking the (+) and (-) button on the leftmost side of the map, or may zoom in and out using a mouse.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-358 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_02-Zoom-In.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Important Map Tools</span>  </h3>\r\n\r\nThere are several tools that can be accessed using the map. These tools allow the user to view data more efficiently by providing different ways to filter and access data.\r\n\r\n<h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/filtering-and-searching/\" xlink=\"href\">Filters</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-349 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"199\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Filters_Layers_01.png\" width=\"800\">DRIVER lets users narrow down their searches in order to easily find specific incident entries or sets of incident entries within the DRIVER database. They may choose between filtering the map towards only a specific area, or the severity of the incident, etc\r\n\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\">\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-345 size-full\" height=\"475\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Layers_Only.png\" style=\"width: 246px; height: auto;\" width=\"246\">\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/layers/\" xlink=\"href\">Layers</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nUnlike Filters, setting a layer lets users choose what kind of incident data they want to access:&nbsp; Incidents, Interventions, Heatmap, Blackspots, City/Province, or Region. Users may also choose between viewing the Street View or the Satelite View.&nbsp; Users can choose more than one layer, or a combination of layers to further narrow down their searches.\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n<div class=\"pbs-row\" style=\"min-height: 200px;\"><div class=\"pbs-col\" style=\"flex-basis: 50%; justify-content: center;\"><h3>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/graphs-2/\" xlink=\"href\">Graphs</a>  </h3>\r\n\r\nGraphs are available on the Map Interface by selecting the bottom left corner of the page, where a tab can be found that expands to display graphs.\r\n\r\nUsers may toggle between graph styles using the button at the top right of the chart. The data loaded into the graphs is controlled by the currently applied date range and filter set, including geographic filters.\r\n\r\nThere are two types of graphs. One is a ToDDoW graph similar to the one on the dashboard. The only difference is that the data is filtered according to what the user sets.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-351 size-full\" height=\"291\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Highlight_Graphs_1.png\" width=\"593\">The second graph is the total number of incidents over time, aggregated by week. Both graphs provide interactivity on mouse hover.\r\n\r\n</div></div>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full\" height=\"295\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Hghlight_Graph_2.png\" width=\"600\">\r\n\r\n<h3>  <span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Related Content</span>  </h3>  <ul>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/view-interfaces\" xlink=\"href\">View Interfaces</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/attribute-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Attribute Filters</a>  </li>  <li>  <a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a>  </li>  </ul>[:]', '[:en]Map[:Ph]Map Interface[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '28-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-03 17:07:01', '2017-10-03 17:07:01', '', 28, 'http://roadsafety.ph/28-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
