(906, 1, '2017-10-04 01:22:35', '2017-10-04 01:22:35', '[:en]Analyst users have the ability to edit incident data.\r\n\r\nWhen the Analyst user is logged in on the DRIVER website, they will get access to additional buttons for editing information, which can usually be viewed on the right side of individual incident record windows and popups next to the \"View\" button.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-908 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/EDIT_ANALYST_Button1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"776\" height=\"113\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-909 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/EDIT_ANALYST_Button2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"283\" height=\"157\" />\r\n\r\nClicking on the \"Edit\" button will bring the Analyst user to the Incident Input Form\'s editing mode. From here, an Analyst user may edit data or delete the incident completely.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-911 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/EDIT_ANALYST_Button_Delete.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"284\" height=\"148\" />[:]', '[:en]Editing Data[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'editing-data', '', '', '2017-10-04 01:30:16', '2017-10-04 01:30:16', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=906', 0, 'post', '', 0),
