(918, 1, '2017-10-04 01:40:57', '2017-10-04 01:40:57', '[:en]Analyst users have the ability to assign traffic enforcers on a particular area.\r\n<h3>Assigning Traffic Enforcers</h3>\r\nTo assign traffic enforcers, the Analyst user must first access the Map to draw a rectangular or polygon tool around the area they wish to assign the enforcer to.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-391 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n\r\nAfter this, the user must click on the \"Traffic Enforcement Assignments\" tab at the bottom of the Map. This will prompt a popup to appear that the Analyst user can add details to, such as the names of the enforcers they wish to assign at the particular area.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-917 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ANALYST_Traffic_Enforcer-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"792\" height=\"553\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Traffic Enforcer Assignments[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '913-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 01:40:57', '2017-10-04 01:40:57', '', 913, 'http://roadsafety.ph/913-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(920, 1, '2017-10-04 04:11:23', '2017-10-04 04:11:23', '[:en]The Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\r\n<h3>Using the Rectangular Tool</h3>\r\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />Once on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-390 size-full aligncenter\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_03-Highlight-Tool.gif\" width=\"844\" height=\"468\" />Once selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />Once the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-388 size-full\" style=\"height: auto;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />Users may view more details of the selected incident by clicking on the \"View\" button inside the incident details\' pop-up.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-393 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_06-VIew-Incident.gif\" width=\"800\" height=\"444\" />\r\n<h3>Removing the Rectangle Tool</h3>\r\nTo delete the rectangle tool, click on the rectangle tool button on the leftmost side of he page. Doing this will remove the rectangle the user has drawn on the page, and will leave only the pop-up of the incident button.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-394 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_02-Exit-Rectangular-Tool_01-Remove-Rectangle.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"443\" />\r\n<h1><strong>Related Articles</strong></h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/polygon-tool\" xlink=\"href\">Polygon Tool</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/spatial-filters\" xlink=\"href\">Spatial Filters</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/saving-and-clearing\" xlink=\"href\">Saving &amp; Clearing Filters</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nThe Rectangular Tool lets the user draw a rectangular shape over their selected area, which filters incidents into the selected area only.\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Using the Rectangular Tool</span>  </h1>\r\n\r\nTo draw a boundary with the rectangular tool, click on the “Map” button on the dropdown located at the Dashboard’s header bar.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-357 size-full\" height=\"443\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/01_Map_01-Click-Dashboard.gif\" width=\"800\">Once on the Map Interface, select the the Rectangular Tool icon on the leftmost part of the screen.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"wp-image-390 size-full aligncenter\" height=\"468\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_03-Highlight-Tool.gif\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto;\" width=\"844\">Once selected, use it to draw a rectangular shape anywhere on the map. You may also opt to zoom in before drawing the rectangular shape, as this usually yields more accurate results.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_04-Draw.gif\" width=\"800\">Once the rectangular area is selected, users may select an incident on the map to view.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-388 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_05-Pop-up.gif\" style=\"height: auto;\" width=\"800\">Users may view more details of the selected incident by clicking on the \"View\" button inside the incident details\' pop-up.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-393 size-full\" height=\"444\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/03_Content-Area-Tools_01-Rectangular-Tool_06-VIew-Incident.gif\" width=\"800\">\r\n\r\n<h1>  <span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Removing the Rectangle Tool</span>  </h1>[:]', 'Rectangular Tool', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '403-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 04:11:23', '2017-10-04 04:11:23', '', 403, 'http://roadsafety.ph/403-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(923, 1, '2017-10-04 04:45:48', '2017-10-04 04:45:48', '[:en]Data on the DRIVER site may be further analyzed by exporting Interventions and Incidents into CSV files, which can afterwards be converted into spreadsheet files.\r\n\r\nUnlike Incident Records however, Intervention Data can only be accessed through CSV Exports.\r\n<h3 style=\"color: #333333;\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-892 size-full\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ANALYST_Add_Intervention.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"87\" /></h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-929 size-full\" style=\"display: block; float: none; margin: calc(1rem + 0.5vw) auto; max-height: 100vh !important;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Export_Popup.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"178\" />\r\n<h3>Exporting Incident Records</h3>\r\nIncident Records may be exported by clicking on the \"Export\" tab at the bottom of the map.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-927 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Screenshot_3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"206\" />\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\" itemprop=\"articleBody\">\r\n<div data-editable=\"\" data-name=\"main-content\" class=\"pbs-main-wrapper\">\r\n\r\nThis will prompt you to either click “Add Intervention” or “Export Interventions”. Clicking on the latter will automatically export a CSV file of intervention records.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Exporting Intervention Records</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-928 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Export-Popup-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"161\" />\r\n<div class=\"col-md-12\"><article id=\"post-881\" class=\"row post-881 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized\">\r\n<div class=\"entry-content\" itemprop=\"articleBody\">\r\n<div data-editable=\"\" data-name=\"main-content\" class=\"pbs-main-wrapper\">\r\n\r\nTo export intervention data, click on the “Interventions” tab at the bottom of the Map Interface. This will prompt you to either click “Add Intervention” or “Export Interventions”. Clicking on the latter will automatically export a CSV file of intervention records.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<footer class=\"entry-footer wedocs-entry-footer\">\r\n<div class=\"wedocs-article-author\" itemprop=\"author\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"https://schema.org/Person\"></div>\r\n</footer></article></div>[:]', '[:en]Viewing Data Through Exports[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'viewing-data-through-exports', '', '', '2017-10-04 04:56:07', '2017-10-04 04:56:07', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=923', 0, 'post', '', 0),
