(945, 1, '2017-10-04 05:53:05', '2017-10-04 05:53:05', '[:en]Analyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit and delete already existing data.\r\n<h3>Related Articles</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/user-types-and-roles\" xlink=\"href\">User Types &amp; Roles</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/administrator\" xlink=\"href\">Admin</a></li>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"http://roadsafety.ph/public-viewer\" xlink=\"href\">Public Viewer</a></li>\r\n</ul>[:Ph]\r\nAnalyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit data already existing data.\r\n\r\nManaging Duplicate Records\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Analyst[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 05:53:05', '2017-10-04 05:53:05', '', 298, 'http://roadsafety.ph/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(946, 1, '2017-10-04 05:58:58', '2017-10-04 05:58:58', '[:en]Analyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit and delete already existing data.\r\n<h3>Add, Edit, and Delete Data</h3>\r\nAn analyst user\'s interface on the DRIVER website gets additional analyst-exclusive features, such as buttons to add, edit, and delete incident and intervention reports.\r\n<h3>Access to Additional Data</h3>\r\nAdditional data is also accessible by the Analyst user. Examples include access to vehicle information, persons involved in the incident, and photos of the incidents.\r\n<h3>Export Data as CSV files</h3>\r\nAssign Traffic Enforcers to a Selected Area[:Ph]\r\nAnalyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit data already existing data.\r\n\r\nManaging Duplicate Records\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]What is an Analyst?[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 05:58:58', '2017-10-04 05:58:58', '', 298, 'http://roadsafety.ph/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(947, 1, '2017-10-04 06:02:19', '2017-10-04 06:02:19', '[:en]Analyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit and delete already existing data.\r\n<h3>Add, Edit, and Delete Data</h3>\r\nAn analyst user\'s interface on the DRIVER website gets additional analyst-exclusive features, such as buttons to add, edit, and delete incident and intervention reports.\r\n<h3>Access to Additional Data and Filters</h3>\r\nAdditional data is also accessible by the Analyst user. Examples include access to vehicle information, persons involved in the incident, and photos of the incidents. Aside from this, Analysts also have an additional filter to narrow down searches according to vehicle type.\r\n<h3>Export Data as CSV files</h3>\r\nAnalysts also have the ability to export data as CSV files, which can be downloaded and converted into spreadsheets for further data analysis.\r\n<h3>Assign Traffic Enforcers to a Selected Area</h3>\r\nAnalysts also have the ability to assign traffic enforcers to selected areas via the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:Ph]\r\nAnalyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit data already existing data.\r\n\r\nManaging Duplicate Records\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Analyst User Overview[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 06:02:19', '2017-10-04 06:02:19', '', 298, 'http://roadsafety.ph/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(948, 1, '2017-10-04 06:05:52', '2017-10-04 06:05:52', '[:en]Occasionally, two users may input the same incident. DRIVER has a process that runs on record creation and nightly to identify potential duplicate incidents. Admin and Analyst users may access an interface to identify and resolve the duplicates.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-440 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Manage-Duplicate-Records.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"637\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAfter choosing to resolve a potential duplicate, the users are presented with data from each record, and may choose to use one or the other, or keep both records.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-439 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Manage-Duplicate-Records-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1366\" height=\"637\" />[:Ph]\r\nOccasionally, two users may input the same incident. DRIVER has a process that runs on record creation and nightly to identify potential duplicate incidents. Admin users may access an interface to identify and resolve the duplicates.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;text-decoration:underline;\">SCREENSHOT HERE</span>\r\n\r\nAfter choosing to resolve a potential duplicate, the users are presented with data from each record, and may choose to use one or the other, or keep both records.\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Duplicate Record Management[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '245-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 06:05:52', '2017-10-04 06:05:52', '', 245, 'http://roadsafety.ph/245-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(949, 1, '2017-10-04 06:06:44', '2017-10-04 06:06:44', '[:en]Analyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit and delete already existing data.\r\n<h3>Add, Edit, and Delete Data</h3>\r\nAn analyst user\'s interface on the DRIVER website gets additional analyst-exclusive features, such as buttons to add, edit, and delete incident and intervention reports.\r\n<h3>Access to Additional Data and Filters</h3>\r\nAdditional data is also accessible by the Analyst user. Examples include access to vehicle information, persons involved in the incident, and photos of the incidents. Aside from this, Analysts also have an additional filter to narrow down searches according to vehicle type.\r\n<h3>Export Data as CSV files</h3>\r\nAnalysts also have the ability to export data as CSV files, which can be downloaded and converted into spreadsheets for further data analysis.\r\n<h3>Manage Duplicate Records</h3>\r\nOccasionally, two users may input the same incident. DRIVER has a process that runs on record creation and nightly to identify potential duplicate incidents. Admin and Analyst users may access an interface to identify and resolve the duplicates.\r\n<h3>Assign Traffic Enforcers to a Selected Area</h3>\r\nAnalysts also have the ability to assign traffic enforcers to selected areas via the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:Ph]\r\nAnalyst users have additional access to certain parts of DRIVER, and can both view and input data, as well as edit data already existing data.\r\n\r\nManaging Duplicate Records\r\n\r\n[:]', '[:en]Analyst User Overview[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '298-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-04 06:06:44', '2017-10-04 06:06:44', '', 298, 'http://roadsafety.ph/298-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(950, 1, '2017-10-04 07:15:06', '2017-10-04 07:15:06', '[:en]The DRIVER application includes functionality to generate custom reports from the database. These reports aggregate counts of incidents according to the rows and columns defined by users generating the reports.\r\n\r\nThe reports also allow for geographic aggregation based on any uploaded boundary layers.\r\n<h3>How to Add Custom Reports</h3>\r\nFrom the Map, click on the \"Export\" tab on the bottom of the page.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-958 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Add_Custom_Report.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"194\" />\r\n\r\nClicking on this will a pop-up window that provides the user with the option to organize reports by using rows and columns to specify details according to Filter, Geographic, and Date &amp; Time from the data fields defined in the schema.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-959 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Add_Custom_Report2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"784\" height=\"450\" />\r\n\r\nThe user may also able to specify a geographic aggregation to break the counts of incidents out by the regions of a boundary layer.\r\n\r\nNote that any filters that are active for the application will apply to the results of the report.[:]', '[:en]Generate Custom Reports[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'generate-custom-reports', '', '', '2017-10-04 08:15:11', '2017-10-04 08:15:11', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=950', 0, 'post', '', 0),
