(1001, 1, '2017-10-05 15:40:41', '2017-10-05 15:40:41', '[:en]<h3>Viewing Incidents by Road Vulnerability</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-999 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/03_FURNISH_01_Remove-Username_Road-Vulnerability_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"634\" />\r\n\r\nBlack spots are sections of roadway or intersections that experience an unusually high number of traffic\r\ncrashes.\r\n\r\nTo view the black spots of a particular area, go to the Map interface of the page, select the layers button, and tick \"Black Spots.\"\r\n<h3>Viewing Incidents by Severity</h3>\r\n<h3><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1000 size-full\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/03_FURNISH_02_Remove-Username_Road-Vulnerability_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1364\" height=\"636\" /></h3>\r\nThe heatmap represents the volume of the severity of incidents in a particular area.\r\n\r\nTo use the heatmap go to the Map, select the layers button, and tick \"Heat map\".\r\n\r\nThe heat map and black spots may also be used together with other filters on the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Road Vulnerability[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '827-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 15:40:41', '2017-10-05 15:40:41', '', 827, 'http://roadsafety.ph/827-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
