(1015, 1, '2017-10-05 15:52:56', '2017-10-05 15:52:56', '[:en]Data on interventions may also be exported from the DRIVER website as a set of CSV files. As with exporting incident data, The export CSV zip file contains a CSV for each type of related object, linked to the primary accident table via a unique ID. The CSV files also contain the latitude and longitude for the incident location. These files may be further analyzed using spreadsheet or database software.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-883 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ANALYST_Export_Intervention_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"111\" />\r\n\r\nTo export intervention data, click on the \"Interventions\" tab at the bottom of the Map Interface. This will prompt you to either click \"Add Intervention\" or \"Export Interventions\". Click on the latter, which will automatically download the CSV file.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1013 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/11_NEW_02_Highlight-Export-Interventions_Exporting-Interventions_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"222\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Exporting Interventions[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '881-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 15:52:56', '2017-10-05 15:52:56', '', 881, 'http://roadsafety.ph/881-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1016, 1, '2017-10-05 15:55:05', '2017-10-05 15:55:05', '[:en]Data on interventions may also be exported from the DRIVER website as a set of CSV files. As with exporting incident data, The export CSV zip file contains a CSV for each type of related object, linked to the primary accident table via a unique ID. The CSV files also contain the latitude and longitude for the incident location. These files may be further analyzed using spreadsheet or database software.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-883 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ANALYST_Export_Intervention_1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"111\" />\r\n\r\nTo export intervention data, click on the \"Interventions\" tab at the bottom of the Map Interface. This will prompt you to either click \"Add Intervention\" or \"Export Interventions\". Click on the latter, which will automatically download the CSV file. As with exporting other data from DRIVER, you may convert this into a spreadsheet file using an external software for further analysis.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1013 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/11_NEW_02_Highlight-Export-Interventions_Exporting-Interventions_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"222\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Exporting Interventions[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '881-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 15:55:05', '2017-10-05 15:55:05', '', 881, 'http://roadsafety.ph/881-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
