(1018, 1, '2017-10-05 15:57:14', '2017-10-05 15:57:14', '[:en]Interventions made regarding the incidents may also be recorded in DRIVER. Analyst users have the ability to add intervention records within the database.\r\n<h3>Accessing the Intervention Input Form</h3>\r\n<img class=\"alignnone wp-image-1009 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/08_FURNISH_01_Highlight-Interventions_Adding-Interventions_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"85\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTo add an Intervention, click on the \"Interventions\" tab at the bottom of the Map interface. A popup will appear that will prompt you to click on either \"Export Interventions\" or \"Add Intervention\". Click on the latter.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1017 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/11_NEW_03_Highlight-Add-Intervention_Exporting-Interventions_EDITED-01-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"222\" />\r\n\r\nThis will prompt a new window to appear called \"Intervention Input Form\"\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1010 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/08_FURNISH_02_Remove-Username_03_Remove-Glitch_Adding-Interventions_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1366\" height=\"1203\" />\r\n\r\nFrom here, Analyst users may select the type of intervention made through a dropdown list available in the \"Intervention Detail\" category.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1011 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/08_FURNISH_02_Remove-Username_Adding-Interventions_EDITED-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"588\" />\r\n\r\nClicking on \"Save Intervention\" will then add the intervention on the DRIVER database.[:]', '[:en]Adding Interventions[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '891-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-05 15:57:14', '2017-10-05 15:57:14', '', 891, 'http://roadsafety.ph/891-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1021, 1, '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '[:en]Admin users of DRIVER have the ability to add fields and subfields to already existing input forms in the website. In the Aschlar Schema Editor, the fields are refered to as Record Types.\r\n<h3>Adding Record Types</h3>\r\nThere are two ways to add a Record Type via the Aschlar Schema Editor. One is via the \"Add Record Type\" link available on the dropdown sidebar, and the other by accessing the \"All Record Types\" section and clicking on the \"Add new type\" button located at the far right of the window. Clicking on this will prompt a new section to open labelled \"Add New Record Type.\"\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1022 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Add-New-Record-Type.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe admin user mus also provide the single and plural title of the Record Type they wish to add onto the DRIVER website. For example, if the user would like to add a new record type called \"Incident\", the Plural Title must be inputted on the field as \"Incidents\".\r\n\r\nClicking the \"Save\" button below will save the new record type and apply it onto the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Adding Fields[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'adding-fields', '', '', '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=1021', 0, 'post', '', 0),
