(1023, 1, '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '[:en]Admin users of DRIVER have the ability to add fields and subfields to already existing input forms in the website. In the Aschlar Schema Editor, the fields are refered to as Record Types.\r\n<h3>Adding Record Types</h3>\r\nThere are two ways to add a Record Type via the Aschlar Schema Editor. One is via the \"Add Record Type\" link available on the dropdown sidebar, and the other by accessing the \"All Record Types\" section and clicking on the \"Add new type\" button located at the far right of the window. Clicking on this will prompt a new section to open labelled \"Add New Record Type.\"\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1022 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Add-New-Record-Type.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1365\" height=\"640\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe admin user mus also provide the single and plural title of the Record Type they wish to add onto the DRIVER website. For example, if the user would like to add a new record type called \"Incident\", the Plural Title must be inputted on the field as \"Incidents\".\r\n\r\nClicking the \"Save\" button below will save the new record type and apply it onto the DRIVER website.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;[:]', '[:en]Adding Fields[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1021-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '2017-10-06 09:30:15', '', 1021, 'http://roadsafety.ph/1021-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1024, 1, '2017-10-06 09:42:27', '2017-10-06 09:42:27', '[:en]<h3>Viewing Record Types</h3>\r\nTo view and edit record types on the Schema Editor, the user must click on \"View All Record Types\" on the Editor\'s sidebar to the left.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1027 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/View-Record-Types.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"351\" />\r\n<h3>Editing Record Types</h3>\r\nFrom the \"View All Record Types\" window, admin users may click on the name of the record type itself to edit the details within it. Another way to edit record types is by clicking on the \"Edit\" button found on the right side of the screen. From here, users may add in the singular and plural forms of their chosen record type label. For instance, if the user wishes to name the new record type \"Incidents\", they must set \"Incident\" as the singular label of the record type, and \"Incidents\" as the plural label.\r\n\r\nThese labels will adjust accordingly on the DRIVER website, depending on whether a DRIVER user adds one or multiple entries.[:]', '[:en]Viewing & Editing Record Types[:]', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'viewing-editing-record-types', '', '', '2017-10-06 13:11:34', '2017-10-06 13:11:34', '', 0, 'http://roadsafety.ph/?p=1024', 0, 'post', '', 0),
