(1028, 1, '2017-10-06 09:42:27', '2017-10-06 09:42:27', '[:en]<h3>Viewing Record Types</h3>\r\nTo view and edit record types on the Schema Editor, the user must click on \"View All Record Types\" on the Editor\'s sidebar to the left.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1027 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/View-Record-Types.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"351\" />\r\n<h3>Editing Record Types</h3>\r\nFrom the \"View All Record Types\" window, admin users may click on the name of the record type itself to edit the details within it. Another way to edit record types is by clicking on the \"Edit\" button found on the right side of the screen. From here, users may add in the singular and plural forms of their chosen record type label. For instance, if the user wishes to name the new record type \"Incidents\", they must set \"Incident\" as the singular label of the record type, and \"Incidents\" as the plural label. These labels will adjust accordingly on the DRIVER website, depending on whether a DRIVER user adds one or multiple entries.[:]', '[:en]Viewing & Editing Record Types[:]', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1024-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-10-06 09:42:27', '2017-10-06 09:42:27', '', 1024, 'http://roadsafety.ph/1024-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
