(1141, 1, '2017-10-10 10:55:29', '2017-10-10 10:55:29', '[:en]In order to input, edit, and delete data on the DRIVER website, the user must have Analyst privileges. The application for Analyst users are as follows:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Before registering, assign a road safety data officer/group who will input and update data on DRIVER.</li>\r\n 	<li>Create a Gmail account for DRIVER access. Kindly follow this format:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>roadsafety.&lt;your city/municipality/province&gt;@gmail.com</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong> (Example: roadsafety.pasig@gmail.com)</strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n 	<li>Submit a letter of intent (See Annex A or <u>http://bit.ly/2u0QDDb</u>) in pdf format at roadsafety.dotr@gmail.com. This will prompt DOTr to give Analyst access/privileges to the local government unit\'s (LGU) registered road safety Gmail account.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n 	<li>Wait for DOTr’s email/text notification of analyst account activation.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n 	<li>Log-in to your road safety Gmail account then access <strong>roadsafety.gov.ph</strong>. Press “Log-in with google.com”, and use the gmail address you used to register for DRIVER. After this, you will be automatically taken to the DRIVER dashboard.<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-1144 size-full\" src=\"http://roadsafety.ph/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/driver-login.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"912\" height=\"477\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;[:tl]Para makapag <em>input, edit</em> at mag-<em>delete</em> ng datos sa DRIVER website, dapat ang gumagamit ay mayroong pribilehiyong pang-<em>Analyst. </em>Ang mga sumusunod ang mga hakbang upang maging <em>Analyst</em>:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Bago mag-<em>register,</em> magtalaga ng isang/grupo ng mga opisyal na maglalagay ng datos sa DRIVER.</li>\r\n 	<li>Gamitin ang Gmail account para mabuksan ang DRIVER. Paki sundan ang ayos sa ibaba:</li>\